/m/07bm98.description: A class for sounds that reveal the particular equipment used to capture or reproduce the sound.
/m/07bm98.name: Sound reproduction

/m/0fx80y.description: Sounds of a musical instrument using tensioned strings to produce tones, where the usual mode of playing is to pull and release the strings to cause them to vibrate.
/m/0fx80y.comments_JP: Father has a few examples, children populate this class
/m/0fx80y.name: Plucked string instrument

/m/07r4wb8.description: A sharp noise of a rigid surface being struck, usually without damage and deliberately, most often with the knuckles of the hand.
/m/07r4wb8.name: Knock

/m/05_wcq.description: Sounds caused by a bird's use of its wings to travel through the air.
/m/05_wcq.name: Bird flight, flapping wings

/m/04_sv.description: Sounds of a small motor vehicle, usually with only two wheels. Motorcycles typically lack an external shell and seat riders astride the engine.
/m/04_sv.name: Motorcycle

/m/028ght.description: Group expression of approval by the collective act of clapping by a group.
/m/028ght.name: Applause

/m/07plz5l.description: An utterance made by exhaling audibly.
/m/07plz5l.name: Sigh

/m/01z47d.description: A sound (usually a simple repeating tone) played over a telephone line to indicate that the requested connection could not be completed, for instance because the remote party is already engaged in a different call.
/m/01z47d.name: Busy signal

/m/030rvx.description: Sounds of a mechanical, electromechanical, or piezoelectric signaling device that emits a steady, highly-audible tone with a spectrum extending to high frequencies.
/m/030rvx.name: Buzzer

/m/0fx9l.description: Sounds made by a kitchen appliance that heats food by exposing it to microwave radiation, including the noise of the fan, rotation mechanism, and microwave source, as well as the alert sound used to indicate that cooking is complete.
/m/0fx9l.name: Microwave oven

/m/012f08.description: Sounds of self-propelled land vehicles, usually wheeled, that do not operate on rails. Includes "off-road" vehicles designed for unmade roads.
/m/012f08.name: Motor vehicle (road)

/m/07phhsh.description: A loud, low-pitched, dull, continuous noise.
/m/07phhsh.name: Rumble

/m/05rwpb.description: Music produced independent of major commercial record labels, possibly including a do-it-yourself approach to recording and publishing. The term indie is also used to describe music of this style regardless of actual production channel.
/m/05rwpb.comments_JP: Ill-defined class. No examples in FS. Remove.
/m/05rwpb.name: Independent music

/m/07s0dtb.description: A short labored intake of breath with the mouth open. Often indicates shock or surprise.
/m/07s0dtb.name: Gasp

/g/122z_qxw.description: The sound of a small explosive device primarily designed to produce a large amount of noise, especially in the form of a loud bang.
/g/122z_qxw.name: Firecracker

/m/074ft.description: A musical work intended to be sung by the human voice with distinct and fixed pitches and patterns using sound and silence and a variety of forms that often include the repetition of sections.
/m/074ft.name: Song

/m/0ggq0m.description: Art music produced or rooted in the traditions of Western music, including both liturgical and secular music, over the broad span of time from roughly the 11th century to the present day.
/m/0ggq0m.name: Classical music

/m/01bjv.description: Interior and exterior sounds of a road vehicle designed to carry many passengers.
/m/01bjv.name: Bus

/t/dd00002.description: The sound of a young child crying or bawling.
/t/dd00002.name: Baby cry, infant cry

/m/03vt0.description: Sounds associated with invertebrates from the arthropod phylum that have a chitinous exoskeleton, a three-part body, three pairs of jointed legs, compound eyes, and one pair of antennae.
/m/03vt0.name: Insect

/m/01gp74.description: Any musical set of usually three or more notes that is heard as if sounding simultaneously.
/m/01gp74.name: Chord

/m/018j2.description: Sounds of a 4-, 5-, or 6-stringed instrument with a thin membrane stretched over a frame or cavity as a resonator, called the head.
/m/018j2.name: Banjo

/t/dd00034.description: Music that evokes or conveys feelings of tenderness.
/t/dd00034.name: Tender music

/m/0l15bq.description: A percussive sound made by a human striking together the palms of their two hands, often quickly and repeatedly to express appreciation or approval. This category is to be used for distinct claps by a single person; for a group of people clapping together, use Applause.
/m/0l15bq.name: Clapping

/t/dd00091.description: Sounds that suggest the involvement of electronic audio processing equipment.
/t/dd00091.name: Sound equipment

/m/020w2.description: The sound of a brass instrument distinguished from a trumpet by its conical bore, more compact shape, and mellower tone quality.
/m/020w2.comments_JP: Possibly merge with Bugle. Very noisy mapping. Remove?
/m/020w2.name: Cornet

/m/07qn5dc.description: The multi-syllable warning call made by a rooster (male chicken).
/m/07qn5dc.name: Crowing, cock-a-doodle-doo

/t/dd00035.description: Music that evokes or conveys feelings of excitement.
/t/dd00035.name: Exciting music

/m/07pxg6y.description: The sound of a volcano violently ejecting ash and lava, or a similar event in which large volumes of material are explosively released.
/m/07pxg6y.name: Eruption

/m/07k1x.description: Sounds associated with any physical item that can be used to achieve a goal, especially if the item is not consumed in the process.
/m/07k1x.name: Tools

/m/0kpck.description: A genre of Caribbean music that originated in Trinidad and Tobago in the late 1970s as an offshoot of kaiso and calypso, with influences from cadence, funk, and soul.
/m/0kpck.name: Soca music

/m/0btp2.description: The combined sounds of many motor vehicles traveling on roads.
/m/0btp2.name: Traffic noise, roadway noise

/m/026z9.description: A genre of dance music containing elements of funk, soul, pop, and salsa that achieved popularity during the mid-1970s to the early 1980s.
/m/026z9.name: Disco

/m/0838f.description: Sounds caused by motion of liquid water.
/m/0838f.name: Water

/t/dd00110.description: Sounds that are associated with shells, rigid sheets, or other predominantly two-dimensional surfaces.
/t/dd00110.name: Deformable shell

/m/032n05.description: Sounds produced by whales for different kinds of communication.
/m/032n05.name: Whale vocalization

/m/01s0ps.description: Sounds of a music instrument with a piano-style keyboard, where pressing keys causes mechanical hammers to strike metal strings, metal reeds, or wire tines, leading to vibrations which are converted into electrical signals by magnetic pickups.
/m/01s0ps.name: Electric piano

/m/07q4ntr.description: A very loud utterance by a person that seems more animal than human.
/m/07q4ntr.name: Bellow

/m/025wky1.description: The sound of a device that removes heat from the air inside a building or vehicle, thus lowering the air temperature.
/m/025wky1.name: Air conditioning

/m/07pggtn.description: A brief sound as made by a small bird.
/m/07pggtn.name: Chirp, tweet

/m/07rn7sz.description: The sound of a brittle rigid substance rapidly breaking into many pieces.
/m/07rn7sz.name: Shatter

/m/07s12q4.description: The sound of a brittle substance being crushed.
/m/07s12q4.name: Crunch

/t/dd00129.description: Sounds that appear to have been recorded outdoors in a natural, non-manmade environment.
/t/dd00129.name: Outside, rural or natural

/m/07rrh0c.description: A partly dull hollow sound with a damped resonance.
/m/07rrh0c.name: Thunk

/m/0bm02.description: The sound of a large drum that produces a note of low definite or indefinite pitch.
/m/0bm02.name: Bass drum

/m/0m0fw.description: A genre of music that challenges the distinction between musical and non-musical sound with the expressive use of acoustically or electronically generated noise.
/m/0m0fw.comments_JP: Difficult to find examples for this class
/m/0m0fw.name: Noise music

/m/07q8f3b.description: A loud sustained noise caused by wind, resembling the cry of a hound.
/m/07q8f3b.name: Howl (wind)

/m/05tny_.description: Principal communication sound produced by dogs. Often transliterated as woof, especially for large dogs.
/m/05tny_.name: Bark

/m/01280g.description: Sounds associated with animals not normally raised by humans.
/m/01280g.name: Wild animals

/m/03k3r.description: Sounds associated with the familiar domesticated large, fast, and strong ungulate mammal.
/m/03k3r.name: Horse

/m/01j423.description: The sound of a reflex consisting of the simultaneous inhalation of air and the stretching of the eardrums, followed by an exhalation of breath, commonly associated with tiredness. Specifically refers to humans.
/m/01j423.name: Yawn

/m/0g12c5.description: A sound that has been modified in a nonlinear fashion, usually in electronic equipment, to introduce sound correlated with the original signal. In many cases, notably with amplified electric musical instruments, distortion is introduced as an effect by increasing the gain and clipping the source signal.
/m/0g12c5.name: Distortion

/m/07qcpgn.description: The sound of a light collision between a rigid object and a rigid surface, for instance to deliberately attract attention.
comments_EF: difficult to narrow down. will probably be noisy
/m/07qcpgn.name: Tap

/m/07pt6mm.description: The sound of a substance being reduced to small pieces or particles by pounding or abrading, or the sound of two surfaces rubbing with high friction that suggests that one or both surfaces are being disintergrated.
/m/07pt6mm.name: Grind

/m/0chx_.description: A random, unstructured sound in which the value at any moment provides no information about the value at any other moment. White noise has equal energy in all frequency bands.
/m/0chx_.name: White noise

/t/dd00098.description: Portmanteau class for sounds that do not immediately suggest specific source objects, but which are more likely to be perceived and described according to their acoustic properties.
/t/dd00098.name: Source-ambiguous sounds

/m/07c52.description: A sound that appears to have been produced by a television set.
/m/07c52.name: Television

/m/0dl5d.description: A rock music subgenre that developed in the late 1960s as an attempt to give greater artistic credibility to rock music. Songs were replaced by musical suites that often stretched to 20 or 40 minutes in length and contained symphonic influences, extended musical themes, fantasy-like ambience and lyrics, and complex orchestrations.
/m/0dl5d.name: Progressive rock

/m/080nby.description: A type of music and dance developed in Angola in the 1980s sampled from traditional Caribbean carnival music and Angolan semba around a fast, energetic 4/4 beat.
/m/080nby.comments_JP: No examples. Remove class, it is blacklisted.
/m/080nby.name: Kuduro

/m/07rqsjt.description: A sibilant sound caused by a rigid object sweeping through the air.
/m/07rqsjt.name: Whoosh, swoosh, swish

/m/03mb9.description: A genre of electronic dance music originating in Chicago in the early 1980s which is generally dance-based music characterized by repetitive 4/4 beats, rhythms mainly provided by drum machines, off-beat hi-hat cymbals, and synthesized basslines.
/m/03mb9.name: House music

/m/07sx8x_.description: Abrasive, unpleasant sharp sound produced by a bird.
/m/07sx8x_.name: Squawk

/m/07qs1cx.description: Abrupt sounds of individual ruptures in a rigid substance under stress.
/m/07qs1cx.name: Crack

/m/0395lw.description: The sound of a simple instrument usually consisting of metal cast in the shape of a hollow cup, whose sides form a resonator which vibrates in a single tone upon being struck by a "clapper" suspended within, or by a separate mallet or hammer.
/m/0395lw.name: Bell

/m/07p6fty.description: Talk in a loud voice to deliberately command attention or overcome interfering sounds. Does not have the stronger emotional connotations of Yell or Scream.
/m/07p6fty.name: Shout

/m/09d1b1.description: A high frequency noise present on analog magnetic tape recordings caused by the size of the magnetic particles used to make the tape.
/m/09d1b1.name: Tape hiss

/m/04fgwm.description: The sound of a toothbrush that makes rapid, automatic bristle motions driven by an electric motor in order to clean teeth.
/m/04fgwm.name: Electric toothbrush

/m/0326g.description: A genre originating in Andalusian music and dance styles which includes cante, toque, baile, jaleo, palmas, and pitos.
/m/0326g.name: Flamenco

/m/04rmv.description: Sounds associated with the familiar small rodent.
/m/04rmv.name: Mouse

/m/0dxrf.description: The sound of cooking food in oil or another fat.
/m/0dxrf.name: Frying (food)

/t/dd00077.description: Sounds that originate from human-created machinery and devices.
/t/dd00077.name: Mechanisms

/m/06j64v.description: Music originating from the vast region from Morocco to Iran, including the Arabic countries of the Middle East and North Africa, the Iraqi traditions of Mesopotamia, Iranian traditions of Persia, the Hebrew music of Israel, Armenian music, the varied traditions of Cypriot music, the music of Turkey, traditional Assyrian music, Berbers of North Africa, and Coptic Christians in Egypt.
/m/06j64v.name: Middle Eastern music

/m/03gvt.description: Sounds of an electric organ invented by Laurens Hammond and John M. Hanert in which sliding drawbars create a variety of sounds.
/m/03gvt.name: Hammond organ

/m/02pprs.description: The sound of the most common member of the saxophone family covering a mid-range of pitches.
/m/02pprs.name: Alto saxophone

/t/dd00001.description: Laughter that is produced by a baby or infant.
/t/dd00001.name: Baby laughter

/m/07gql.description: The sound of a high-pitched brass instruments played by blowing air through almost-closed lips, producing a "buzzing" sound that starts a standing wave vibration in the air column inside the instrument.
/m/07gql.name: Trumpet

/m/07ptzwd.description: The sound of a liquid being drawn or poured with a pump.
/m/07ptzwd.name: Pump (liquid)

/m/07yv9.description: Sounds of mobile machines that transport people or cargo.
/m/07yv9.name: Vehicle

/m/09ld4.description: Sounds associated with the short-bodied, tailless amphibians composing the order Anura.
/m/09ld4.name: Frog

/m/0k4j.description: Sounds of a self-powered motor vehicle with usually four wheels used for transportation of one to eight people, designed to run primarily on roads.
/m/0k4j.name: Car

/m/0l14l2.description: The sound of an ancient musical horn made of ram's horn, used for Jewish religious purposes.
/m/0l14l2.name: Shofar

/t/dd00133.description: Transient contact sounds that are strongly suggestive of the particular objects involved in the collision.
/t/dd00133.name: Specific impact sounds

/m/01jt3m.description: The sound of a toilet flushing water along with any waste through a drainpipe.
/m/01jt3m.name: Toilet flush

/m/0ltv.description: The sound of one or more motor vehicles engaged in a competition to complete a course as quickly as possible. Specialized race cars include many modifications, often making them much louder than common street vehicles.
/m/0ltv.name: Race car, auto racing

/m/0ch8v.description: Sound made by animals associated with farms and agriculture.
/m/0ch8v.name: Livestock, farm animals, working animals

/m/03l9g.description: Sounds made by a tool or device that delivers a blow to an object. Most hammers are hand tools used to drive nails, fit parts, forge metal, and break apart objects.
/m/03l9g.name: Hammer

/t/dd00112.description: The sound of a rigid but flexible sheet, such as paper or aluminum, buckling into a smaller volume.
/t/dd00112.name: Crumpling, crinkling

/m/07rwj3x.description: A loud hooting cry of exultation or excitement.
/m/07rwj3x.name: Whoop

/t/dd00067.description: The sound of a large, heavy-duty internal combustion engine, such as that which powers a large truck, locomotive, or ship.  Jet engines, steam engines, rocket engines etc. are excluded.
/t/dd00067.name: Heavy engine (low frequency)

/m/04cvmfc.description: A deep, bellowing outburst of sound forced through an open mouth, made by a lion or other "big cat" species.
/m/04cvmfc.name: Roar

/m/02bm9n.description: The sound of a mechanical device that allows continuous linear or rotary motion in only one direction while preventing motion in the opposite direction.
/m/02bm9n.name: Ratchet, pawl

/m/07pyf11.description: The noisy sound of a flexible surface, such as a flag, moving back-and-forth in the air and optionally coming into contact with an adjacent hard surface.
/m/07pyf11.comments_XF: does this include bird flap sounds?
/m/07pyf11.name: Flap

/m/01d380.description: Sounds of a tool used for making holes in various materials via a rotating drill bit.
/m/01d380.name: Drill

/m/0gkd1.description: Sounds of an electro-mechanical, polyphonic tape replay keyboard in which each note is produced by a separate piece of pre-recorded tape, supplied in a corresponding set to simulate a particular instrument.
/m/0gkd1.comments_JP: Very difficult to find a song which is generated with the Mellotron. Remove.
/m/0gkd1.name: Mellotron

/m/07swgks.description: The bubbling sound of water flowing through a narrow constriction, such as from a bottle with a narrow neck.
/m/07swgks.name: Gurgling

/m/0130jx.description: Sounds originating from a bowl-shaped plumbing fixture that stores and drains water and that is used for washing hands, dishwashing, and other purposes.
/m/0130jx.name: Sink (filling or washing)

/m/07mzm6.description: A continuous, coarse, whistling sound produced by obstruction of the respiratory airways during breathing.
/m/07mzm6.name: Wheeze

/m/06rvn.description: The sound of a drum that produces a sharp staccato sound by virtue of metal coils (the "snare") stretched across one of the membranes.
/m/06rvn.name: Snare drum

/m/05229.description: The sound of a group of people who perform instrumental and/or vocal music.
/m/05229.comments_JP: Too broad definition. Almost every sound could fit here.
/m/05229.name: Musical ensemble

/m/01m4t.description: Sounds of a computer peripheral which makes a persistent human readable representation of graphics or text on paper or similar physical media.
/m/01m4t.name: Printer

/m/02rhddq.description: The sound of an electronic warning device fitted to many commercial vehicles to alert pedestrians when the reverse gear is engaged, signaling that the vehicle is likely to move backwards.
/m/02rhddq.comments_XF: don't know how to do better, low recall
/m/02rhddq.name: Reversing beeps

/m/02mk9.description: The sound of a machine designed to produce mechanical energy. Combustion engines burn a fuel to create heat, which then creates a force. Electric motors convert electrical energy into mechanical motion. Other classes of engines include pneumatic motors and clockwork motors.
/m/02mk9.name: Engine

/m/01jg02.description: Noises generated by the beating heart and the resultant flow of blood through it.
/m/01jg02.name: Heart sounds, heartbeat

/m/017gp.description: Low frequency sound energy in the range from 16-256 Hz.
/m/017gp.name: Bass (frequency range)

/m/0ggx5q.description: Music composed specifically to facilitate or accompany dancing. It can be either a whole musical piece or part of a larger musical arrangement.
/m/0ggx5q.name: Dance music

/m/039jq.description: Sounds associated with the non-crystalline amorphous solid that is often transparent and has widespread practical, technological, and decorative uses.
/m/039jq.name: Glass

/m/0glt670.description: Hip hop or rap music formed in the United States in the 1970s and consists of stylized rhythmic music that commonly accompanies rhythmic and rhyming speech ("rapping").
/m/0glt670.comments_JP: very broad class, many hits or isolated sounds that are under the umbrella of hip hop
/m/0glt670.name: Hip hop music

/m/0fqfqc.description: The sound of the opening or closing of a box-shaped container that fits into a piece of furniture in such a way that it can be drawn out horizontally to reach its contents.
/m/0fqfqc.name: Drawer open or close

/m/07s8j8t.description: The sound of an object moving by turning over or rotating.
/m/07s8j8t.name: Roll

/m/0hsrw.description: Sounds of a boat (large or small) propelled partly or entirely by sails.
/m/0hsrw.name: Sailboat, sailing ship

/m/07qwdck.description: A sharp high-pitched resonant sound with a clear decay.
/m/07qwdck.name: Ping

/m/0h0rv.description: Sounds associated with these species of birds having short necks and short, slender bills.
/m/0h0rv.name: Pigeon, dove

/m/07pdjhy.description: The sound of two surfaces moving smoothly over each other with pressure but without excessive friction.
/m/07pdjhy.name: Rub

/m/07qdb04.description: The harsh communication sound made by a duck.
/m/07qdb04.name: Quack

/m/07jdr.description: The sound of one or more coupled vehicles running on a rail track to transport cargo or passengers, propelled by a separate locomotive or individual motors in each railroad car.
/m/07jdr.name: Train

/m/07pb8fc.description: The sound of an engine (typically in an automobile) running without any load and at minimal RPM.
/m/07pb8fc.name: Idling

/m/04qvtq.description: The sound of a siren fitted to a ground vehicle used by police when responding to incidents.
/m/04qvtq.name: Police car (siren)

/m/07pk7mg.description: The sound of a structure shaking unsteadily back and forth, as in response to an impact.
/m/07pk7mg.name: Wobble

/m/01f9gb.description: A genre of electronic music that developed in England in the early 1990s characterized by fast tempos, relatively slow and lyrical reggae-derived basslines, breakbeats, and heavily syncopated percussive loops, samples, and synthesized effects.
/m/01f9gb.comments_JP: Genre too specific. No examples in FS
/m/01f9gb.name: Oldschool jungle

/m/0l14qv.description: Sounds associated with an electronic musical instrument that generates electric signals converted to sound through amplifiers and loudspeakers or headphones. Synthesizers may imitate instruments such as piano, organ, flute, or vocals; or they may generate novel electronic timbres.
/m/0l14qv.name: Synthesizer

/m/02qldy.description: Speech by a single human aimed at an audience (either present or assumed, as in a video blog).
/m/02qldy.name: Narration, monologue

/m/07m2kt.description: The ensemble sound produced by an electronic effects unit which outputs simultaneous versions of the input source with small variations in pitch and timbre.
/m/07m2kt.name: Chorus effect

/m/07pc8lb.description: The sound of a rigid object become separated into pieces or fragments.
/m/07pc8lb.name: Breaking

/m/07rpkh9.description: The classic communication sound made by a cow or bull.
/m/07rpkh9.name: Moo

/m/07r04.description: Sounds of large motor vehicles designed to transport cargo on roads.
/m/07r04.name: Truck

/m/015y_n.description: A form of American music that dominated in the 1930s and 1940s, using a strong rhythm section of double bass and drums as the anchor, a lead section of brass, woodwind, and sometimes stringed instruments, medium to fast tempos, and a "lilting" swing time rhythm.
/m/015y_n.name: Swing music

/m/0bmfpc.description: A genre of electronic music from England in the early 1990s that featuress a tempo around 130 beats per minute with a distinctive 4/4 percussive rhythm, syncopated hi-hats, cymbals, and snares, and occasionally beat-skipping kick drums and altered vocal samples.
/m/0bmfpc.comments_JP: Cannot find examples. Remove this class.
/m/0bmfpc.name: UK garage

/m/07r10fb.description: A sound clearly attributable to a single drop of rain.
/m/07r10fb.name: Raindrop

/m/064t9.description: A genre of popular music that originated in the West during the 1950s and 1960s. Pop music is eclectic, often borrowing elements from urban, dance, rock, Latin, country, and other styles. Songs are typically short to medium-length with repeated choruses, melodic tunes, and hooks.
/m/064t9.name: Pop music

/m/0195fx.description: Sounds of high-capacity electric railways that serve as public transport, generally in urban areas.
/m/0195fx.name: Subway, metro, underground

/m/07q34h3.description: The sound of a gas, such as air, being blown forcefully in a short burst.
/m/07q34h3.name: Puff

/m/02jz0l.description: The sound of a hand-operated valve controlling the release of water, for instance as fitted to a sink or bath, and the resulting water flow.
/m/02jz0l.name: Water tap, faucet

/m/08cyft.description: A broad range of percussive electronic music genres including techno, house, trance, drum and bass, dubstep, and Jersey club produced largely for nightclubs, raves, and festivals, or by disc jockeys in the context of a live mix.
/m/08cyft.name: Electronic dance music

/m/01bns_.description: Sounds of a class of stringed instruments consisting of many strings stretched across a thin, flat body, played by strumming or plucking.
/m/01bns_.name: Zither

/m/02w4v.description: A genre that evolved from traditional music during the 20th century folk revival. One meaning often given is that of old songs with no known composers; another is music that has been transmitted and evolved by a process of oral transmission or performed by custom over a long period of time.
/m/02w4v.name: Folk music

/m/05n1m.description: A class of sounds named to phonetically imitate, resemble, or suggest the sound it describes.
/m/05n1m.name: Onomatopoeia

/t/dd00122.description: A class for sound categories not represented by other classes that are peceived by their sound instead of their source.
/t/dd00122.name: Other sourceless

/m/05rj2.description: The sound of playing cards being manually rearranged into a random order.
/m/05rj2.name: Shuffling cards

/m/0dv3j.description: The sound of a liquid that is reaching the temperature at which it transitions to a vapor, resulting in bubbles emerging at the surface.
/m/0dv3j.name: Boiling

/m/07qmpdm.description: An irregular rattling noise, often produced by rapid movement, consisting of a cluster of transient sounds.
/m/07qmpdm.name: Clatter

/m/0c1dj.description: An artificially created or enhanced sound used to emphasize artistic or other content of films, television shows, live performances, animation, video games, music, or other media.
/m/0c1dj.name: Sound effect

/t/dd00140.description: A soft neighing sound made by a horse.
/t/dd00140.name: Nicker

/t/dd00004.description: Singing produced by an adult human female.
/t/dd00004.comments_XF: Plural or no? Recall problem but solved with population of aso labels
/t/dd00004.name: Female singing

/m/0l14gg.description: Recorded music accompanying a movie, video, TV show, video game, or the like. Although any music can be used in a soundtrack, this specifically refers to music that suggests its use to accompany images, rather than something that happens to have been used that way.
/m/0l14gg.name: Soundtrack music

/m/07r_k2n.description: A sharp high-pitched bark or cry, typically from a miniature dog.
/m/07r_k2n.name: Yip

/m/02yds9.description: A tonal fluttering sound made by cats to indicate contentment or relaxed pleasure.
/m/02yds9.name: Purr

/m/0dls3.description: A subgenre of alternative rock that emerged during the mid-1980s fusing elements of punk rock and heavy metal, such as distorted electric guitars. Lyrics are typically angst-filled, addressing themes such as social alienation, apathy, confinement, and a desire for freedom.
/m/0dls3.name: Grunge

/m/07kc_.description: The sound of an early electronic musical instrument controlled without physical contact via two metal antennas that sense the relative position of the player's hands and control oscillators for frequency with one hand, and amplitude with the other.
/m/07kc_.name: Theremin

/m/0fd3y.description: A genre of music that developed in England in the 1970s from experimental and synthesizer-oriented styles which puts an emphasis on tone and atmosphere over traditional musical structure or rhythm.
/m/0fd3y.name: Ambient music

/m/03p19w.description: The sound of a pneumatic or electro-mechanical tool that combines a hammer directly with a chisel, usually used to break up rock, pavement, and concrete.
/m/03p19w.name: Jackhammer

/m/07s72n.description: A genre of electronic dance music that originated in South London in the late 1990s which generally features sparse, syncopated drum and percussion patterns with bass lines that contain prominent sub bass frequencies.
/m/07s72n.name: Dubstep

/m/04wptg.description: Music played at wedding celebrations, including the ceremony and any festivities before or after the event.
/m/04wptg.comments_JP: No clear examples. And note that any music can be wedding music.
/m/04wptg.name: Wedding music

/m/07r_r9m.description: A loud harsh or strident noise, often a warning sound.
/m/07r_r9m.name: Blare

/m/07pkxdp.description: The act of singing a quiet song to lull a child to sleep.
/m/07pkxdp.name: Lullaby

/m/01b82r.description: Sounds of a tool consisting of a tough blade, wire, or chain with a hard toothed edge, used to cut through material, most often wood.  Includes both manual and motorized saws.
/m/01b82r.name: Sawing

/m/029h7y.description: A genre of electronic music and early hip hop influenced by funk and German and Japanese electropop which typically features drum machines and heavy electronic sounds, usually without vocals. If vocals are present they are delivered in a deadpan manner, often through electronic distortion such as vocoding and talkboxing.
/m/029h7y.comments_JP: Ill-defined class with not many examples in FS
/m/029h7y.name: Electro

/m/07phxs1.description: A high-pitched ringing sound, as of a small metal object being struck.
/m/07phxs1.name: Ding

/t/dd00109.description: Sounds produced by a more extended interaction between two objects or surfaces instead of a collision or bounce.
/t/dd00109.name: Surface contact

/m/07sbbz2.description: A genre of popular music that originated and evolved in the United States during the late 1940s and early 1950s, from a combination of African-American genres such as blues, boogie-woogie, jump blues, jazz, and gospel music, together with Western swing and country music.
/m/07sbbz2.comments_JP: Not many examples. On can find rock, but is different from rock and roll
/m/07sbbz2.name: Rock and roll

/m/04j_h4.description: A genre of music that emerged in East London in the early 2000s as a development of UK garage and jungle.
/m/04j_h4.comments_JP: Too specific class. No clear examples. Remove.
/m/04j_h4.name: Grime music

/m/05zc1.description: Sounds of a wheel on an axle or shaft that is designed to support movement and change of direction of a taut cable or belt along its circumference.
/m/05zc1.name: Pulleys

/t/dd00071.description: Sounds that suggest they have been recorded in the home.
/t/dd00071.name: Domestic sounds, home sounds

/m/0l156k.description: The sound of an instrument that produces sound from a stream of forced air.
/m/0l156k.name: Whistle

/m/07r81j2.description: The yowling sound made by a cat in heat.
/m/07r81j2.name: Caterwaul

/m/01s0vc.description: The sound of a device consisting of two rows of small interlocking teeth for binding the edges of an opening of fabric or other flexible material, like on a garment or a bag.
/m/01s0vc.name: Zipper (clothing)

/m/09ddx.description: Sounds associated with this collection of waterfowl species.
/m/09ddx.name: Duck

/m/03w41f.description: The sound of a large bell usually encountered in churches where it used either to signify the hour or the time for worshippers to go to church.
/m/03w41f.name: Church bell

/m/05x_td.description: The sound of a pneumatic device mounted on large vehicles designed to create an extremely loud noise for signalling purposes.
/m/05x_td.name: Air horn, truck horn

/m/012n7d.description: The sound of a siren fitted to a vehicle used to transport sick or injured people to a hospital or other medical facility.
/m/012n7d.name: Ambulance (siren)

/m/018vs.description: Sounds of a relative of the electric guitar with a longer neck and 4 to 6 strings. The common 4-string bass is usually tuned one octave lower than the four lowest pitched strings of a guitar.
/m/018vs.name: Bass guitar

/m/015jpf.description: The sound of a signal that a telephone exchange or other switching equipment sends to a telephone to confirm that it is ready to initiate a connection.
/m/015jpf.name: Dial tone

/m/019jd.description: Sounds of watercraft designed to float, plane, work, or travel on water.
/m/019jd.name: Boat, Water vehicle

/t/dd00018.description: Common vocalization sound associated with pigs.
/t/dd00018.name: Oink

/m/03t22m.description: The sound of a higher-register variety of the saxophone, popular as a lead instrument in jazz.
/m/03t22m.name: Soprano saxophone

/m/056ks2.description: Sounds of a boat propelled using the motion of oars in the water.
/m/056ks2.name: Rowboat, canoe, kayak

/t/dd00136.description: Muted dog vocalization indicating submission, fear, or pain.
/t/dd00136.name: Whimper (dog)

/m/05pd6.description: The sound of a large instrumental ensemble (a dozen or more people), often used in classical music, that contains sections of string, brass, woodwind, and percussion instruments.
/m/05pd6.name: Orchestra

/m/01jg1z.description: Heart sounds produced by abnormal blood flow across one of the heart valves, typically detected by a stethoscope.
/m/01jg1z.name: Heart murmur

/m/01y3hg.description: Sounds emitted by a device that senses smoke, typically to warn of a fire.
/m/01y3hg.name: Smoke detector, smoke alarm

/m/07pc8l3.description: The sound of a thin and rigid element breaking suddenly and abruptly.
/m/07pc8l3.name: Snap

/m/06_y0by.description: The combined sounds of transport, industrial, and recreational activities.
/m/06_y0by.name: Environmental noise

/m/0cj0r.description: Unstructured noise whose energy decreases with frequency such that equal amounts of energy are distributed in logarithmic bands of frequency, typically octaves.  Pink noise sounds more like a rumble where white noise sounds like a hiss.
/m/0cj0r.name: Pink noise

/m/01swy6.description: A form of singing that involves repeated and rapid changes of pitch between the low-pitch chest register and the high-pitch head register or falsetto.
/m/01swy6.name: Yodeling

/m/0ghcn6.description: A low, guttural vocalization produced by animals as a warning, a sign of aggression, or to express anger.
/m/0ghcn6.name: Growling

/t/dd00089.description: Portmanteau class for sound categories that clearly suggest specific sources not covered in the other categories.
/t/dd00089.name: Miscellaneous sources

/m/0zmy2j9.description: Sounds of fasteners typically consisting of two lineal fabric strips, one featuring tiny hooks, the second consisting of even smaller and "hairier" loops.
/m/0zmy2j9.name: Velcro, hook and loop fastener

/m/0ffhf.description: Sounds associated with the domesticated working animal that is a smaller member of the horse family.
/m/0ffhf.name: Donkey, ass

/m/07rv9rh.description: The sound of a horse's hoofs hitting on a hard surface.
/m/07rv9rh.name: Clip-clop

/m/026fgl.description: The sound of an instrument constructed from suspended tubes, rods, bells, or other objects that are often made of metal or wood along with some type of weight the tubes or rods can strike when they or another wind-catching surface are blown by the natural movement of air outside.
/m/026fgl.name: Wind chime

/m/01fhw5.description: A sound of very low frequency (e.g., below 20 Hz) such that is not perceived, or barely perceived, by human listeners.
/m/01fhw5.name: Infrasound

/t/dd00135.description: The boisterous vocalizations of a group of children, for instance in a playground.
/t/dd00135.comments_XF: Need plural form for that. Maybe add more tags (eg synonyms of 'shout')
/t/dd00135.name: Children shouting

/t/dd00088.description: The sound of a liquid coming out of a pipe or other opening rapidly and in large volumes.
/t/dd00088.name: Gush

/m/025l19.description: A sound that appears to come from a recording of a sound, rather than the original sound itself.
/m/025l19.name: Recording

/m/027m70_.description: The sound of a type of bell which produces a distinctive 'jingle' sound, especially in large numbers. They are commonly produced from a single piece of sheet metal bent into a roughly spherical shape containing a small ball bearing.
/m/027m70_.name: Jingle bell

/m/01yrx.description: Sounds associated with the familiar, furry, domestic carnivorous mammal.
/m/01yrx.name: Cat

/m/07pt_g0.description: A sound that is modulated in short, regular bursts at approximately 1 Hz.  This class is not for heartbeat sounds, use /m/01jg02.
/m/07pt_g0.name: Pulse

/m/07brj.description: The sound of a musical instrument consisting of a frame with pairs of small metal jingles. There is often a drumhead stretched across the frame, and the instrument is usually played by striking the frame or head with the hand.
/m/07brj.name: Tambourine

/m/012ndj.description: The sound of a siren fitted to a vehicle used to transport firefighters and their equipment to an emergency situation.
/m/012ndj.name: Fire engine, fire truck (siren)

/m/07p6mqd.description: The sound of small waves of liquid held in a container breaking against the edges.
/m/07p6mqd.name: Slosh

/m/09x0r.description: Speech is the vocalized form of human communication, created out of the phonetic combination of a limited set of vowel and consonant speech sound units.
/m/09x0r.name: Speech

/m/07qjznl.description: A steady recurrent ticking sound as made by a clock.
/m/07qjznl.name: Tick-tock

/m/0cfpc.description: A sound that appears to have been produced by a loudspeaker.
/m/0cfpc.name: Loudspeaker

/m/03cl9h.description: Sounds of a commercial vehicle that serves as a mobile retail outlet for ice cream, usually during the summer. Ice cream vans often play a repeating nursery-rhyme-style melody from speakers mounted on the vehicle's exterior to attract customers.
/m/03cl9h.name: Ice cream truck, ice cream van

/m/02mscn.description: Music that has been written to express either personal or a communal belief regarding Christian life and faith. Its forms vary widely across the world, according to culture and social context.
/m/02mscn.name: Christian music

/t/dd00125.description: Sounds that appear to have been recorded within a small room, such as one that can accommodate no more than 15 people.
/t/dd00125.name: Inside, small room

/m/07rv4dm.description: A loud, resonant, discordant noise, as of a large and partly hollow metal structure begin struck.
/m/07rv4dm.name: Clang

/m/02021.description: Sounds associated with the small, striped rodents of the family Sciuridae.
/m/02021.name: Chipmunk

/m/0j2kx.description: The sound of water flowing over a vertical drop or a series of drops in the course of a stream or river.
/m/0j2kx.name: Waterfall

/m/01hgjl.description: The sound of a technique of moving a vinyl record back and forth on a turntable while optionally manipulating the crossfader on a DJ mixer.
/m/01hgjl.name: Scratching (performance technique)

/m/0cfdd.description: Sounds of an electronic musical instrument designed to imitate the sound of drums, cymbals, other percussion instruments, and often basslines.
/m/0cfdd.comments_JP: Many drum kits are drum machines. Remove this distinction by far?
/m/0cfdd.name: Drum machine

/m/0l14_3.description: Sounds of the subcategory of string instruments that are usually played by a bow rubbing the strings.  Examples may include other playing techniques for these instruments, such as plucking.
/m/0l14_3.name: Bowed string instrument

/m/015lz1.description: Musical sounds produced with the human voice, including sustained tonality, rhythm, and a variety of other vocal techniques.
/m/015lz1.name: Singing

/m/03wvsk.description: The sound of an electromechanical device designed to blow normal or hot air over damp hair, in order to dry the hair.
/m/03wvsk.name: Hair dryer

/m/03lty.description: A genre of rock music that developed in the late 1960s and early 1970s, consisting of a thick, massive sound, characterized by highly amplified distortion, extended guitar solos, emphatic beats, and overall loudness.
/m/03lty.name: Heavy metal

/m/06by7.description: A genre of popular music that originated as "rock and roll" in the United States in the 1950s, and developed into a range of different styles in the 1960s and later. Compared to pop music, rock places a higher degree of emphasis on musicianship, live performance, and an ideology of authenticity.
/m/06by7.name: Rock music

/m/07szfh9.description: A loud, confusing, disagreeable sound, such as many voices shouting simultaneously.
/m/07szfh9.name: Cacophony

/t/dd00121.description: A bouncing or spring-like sound with a tonal component that sweeps upwards.
/t/dd00121.name: Boing

/m/08j51y.description: The sound of a small, high-speed drill used during dental procedures, usually to remove decay and shape tooth structure prior to the insertion of a filling or crown.
/m/08j51y.name: Dental drill, dentist's drill

/m/07qf0zm.description: The long plaintive cry of a dog, wolf, or other canidae.
/m/07qf0zm.name: Howl

/m/03wwcy.description: The sound of a signaling device typically placed near a building's entrance with which a visitor can announce their presence to occupants.
/m/03wwcy.name: Doorbell

/m/01w250.description: High-pitched tone produced by blowing or sucking air through a small opening between the lips. Used to draw attention, as a personal tic, and to reproduce a melody.
/m/01w250.comments_XF: Low recall here. Complicated because 'Whistling' can refer to different stuff
/m/01w250.name: Whistling

/m/01h8n0.description: Interactive, spontaneous spoken communication between two or more people.
/m/01h8n0.name: Conversation

/m/07pdhp0.description: Gripping or chewing off with the teeth and jaws.
/m/07pdhp0.name: Biting

/m/0160x5.description: Sounds associated with the human function of eating and processing nutrition (food).
/m/0160x5.name: Digestive

/m/01hnzm.description: The synthesized or pre-recorded sounds made by contemporary electronic telephones to indicate an incoming call or text message.
/m/01hnzm.name: Ringtone

/m/0dgbq.description: The sound of a siren used to provide emergency population warning of approaching danger such as hurricanes, earthquakes, or military attacks.
/m/0dgbq.name: Civil defense siren

/m/0912c9.description: The sound of a motor vehicle accessory whose purpose is to provide an audible alert of the vehicle's presence.
/m/0912c9.name: Vehicle horn, car horn, honking

/m/02mfyn.description: The loud sound of an electronic device installed in a vehicle in an attempt to discourage theft of the vehicle or its contents.
/m/02mfyn.name: Car alarm

/m/01b9nn.description: The sound of an acoustic environment that includes substantial reflection from multiple walls or other hard surfaces. Reverberation is generally perceived as being able to 'hear' the presence and size of the room or space in which the sound is made.  The reflected sounds should remain audible for hundreds of milliseconds or longer.
/m/01b9nn.name: Reverberation

/m/0y64j.description: The sound of a simple brass instrument with no valves or other pitch-altering devices. All pitch control is done by varying the player's embouchure.
/m/0y64j.comments_JP: Not clear difference between trompet. Merge with cornet?
/m/0y64j.name: Bugle

/m/01www.description: A sound which appears to come from a digital audio Compact Disc.
/m/01www.name: Compact disc

/m/052smk.description: A minimalist genre of music that emphasizes the use of sustained or repeated sounds, notes, or tone-clusters with relatively slight harmonic variations.
/m/052smk.name: Drone music

/m/07qz6j3.description: A plaintive, whining vocalization with some abrupt changes in loudness.
/m/07qz6j3.name: Whimper

/m/0kc2j.description: A repeating section of sound material, usually in electroacoustical music.
/m/0kc2j.name: Loop

/m/042v_gx.description: Sounds of a guitar that produces sound acoustically by transmitting the vibration of the strings from its body to the air. Includes guitars with both nylon (or gut) strings, and those with steel strings.
/m/042v_gx.name: Acoustic guitar

/m/0xzly.description: The sound of a specific kind of rattle that appears in many genres of Caribbean and Latin music. Players hold them by their handles, usually in pairs, and shake them.
/m/0xzly.name: Maraca

/m/07xzm.description: Sounds of a small four-stringed guitar-like instument that originated in Hawaii.
/m/07xzm.name: Ukulele

/m/0k5j.description: Sound of vehicles that fly by gaining support from the air.
/m/0k5j.name: Aircraft

/m/0261r1.description: Speech-like sounds uttered by a human that lack the deeper structure and meaning of conventional speech. Babbling is a stage in a child's development of language.
/m/0261r1.name: Babbling

/m/013y1f.description: Sounds of a keyboard instrument of one or more pipe divisions, each played with its own keyboard, played either with the hands on a keyboard or with the feet using pedals. Unlike the piano, organ notes typically sustain while the key is depressed, rather than dying away.
/m/013y1f.name: Organ

/m/07qsvvw.description: The sound of an enclosure holding gas or liquid coming open suddenly and violently.
/m/07qsvvw.name: Burst, pop

/m/0pv6y.description: A sound perceived when no external sound is present, often described as ringing, usually related to short-term trauma or longer-lasting damage to the ear.
/m/0pv6y.name: Tinnitus, ringing in the ears

/m/015vgc.description: A system of music commonly associated with the southern India, whose main emphasis is on vocal music. Although improvisation plays an important role, Carnatic music is mainly sung through compositions.
/m/015vgc.name: Carnatic music

/m/02g901.description: The sound of a bladed tool primarily used in the removal of unwanted body hair where the blades are continually moved by an electric motor.
/m/02g901.name: Electric shaver, electric razor

/m/01g50p.description: The sound of a vehicle used for carrying cargo or passengers on a rail transport system.
/m/01g50p.name: Railroad car, train wagon

/m/07qfr4h.description: Loud, disordered, unintelligible speech noise from many sources.
/m/07qfr4h.name: Hubbub, speech noise, speech babble

/t/dd00038.description: Steady sound of many rain drops striking a surface such as a roof or window.
/t/dd00038.name: Rain on surface

/m/0h9mv.description: The high-pitched sound of a rubber vehicle tire sliding over a road surface when the torque applied to the wheel (to either accelerate or decelerate) exceeds the maximum frictional force that can be supported.
/m/0h9mv.name: Tire squeal

/m/04zjc.description: Sounds of a fully automatic mounted or portable firearm, designed to fire bullets in quick succession from an ammunition belt or magazine, typically at a rate of 300 to 1800 rounds per minute.
/m/04zjc.name: Machine gun

/m/03t3fj.description: The sound of an accented snare drum beat produced by simultaneously hitting the rim and head of a drum with a drum stick.
/m/03t3fj.name: Rimshot

/m/07hvw1.description: A sound that appears to have been recorded in some specific environment, usually with the intention of capturing and representing that environment.
/m/07hvw1.name: Field recording

/m/02z32qm.description: The sound of the simultaneous and continuous firing of a group of firearms on command.
/m/02z32qm.name: Fusillade

/m/03kmc9.description: The sound of a loud noise-making device used to provide warnings to people nearby. A siren typically consists of a single pitch that changes either smoothly or abruptly on timescales around one second.
/m/03kmc9.name: Siren

/t/dd00123.description: A class for sound categories that suggest information about attributes other than the foreground or target objects.
/t/dd00123.name: Channel, environment and background

/m/02l6bg.description: The sound of an aircraft propulsion system that converts rotary motion from an engine via a rotating set of blades into forward thrust through the air.
/m/02l6bg.name: Propeller, airscrew

/m/07pqn27.description: The sound of an elastic, non-destructive collision in which one or both objects spring back. Depending on the situation, there may be multiple such collisions in a characteristic pattern, as of a ball bouncing.
/m/07pqn27.name: Bouncing

/m/0mbct.description: The sound of a musical percussion instrument consisting of a flat, circular metal disc which is hit with a mallet.
/m/0mbct.name: Gong

/m/01g90h.description: A rumbling, growling or gurgling noise produced by movement of the contents of the gastro-intestinal tract.
/m/01g90h.name: Stomach rumble

/m/06j6l.description: A genre of popular African-American music that originated in the 1940s as urbane, rocking, jazz based music with a heavy, insistent beat. Lyrics focus heavily on the themes of triumphs and failures in terms of relationships, freedom, economics, aspirations, and sex.
/m/06j6l.name: Rhythm and blues

/m/026t6.description: The sound of an instrument consisting of at least one membrane, called a drumhead or drum skin, that is stretched over a shell and struck, either directly with the player's hands, or with a drum stick, to produce sound.
/m/026t6.name: Drum

/m/0l14md.description: The sound of a musical instrument that is sounded by being struck or scraped by a beater; struck, scraped or rubbed by hand; or struck against another similar instrument.
/m/0l14md.name: Percussion

/m/02hnl.description: Sounds of a collection of drums and other percussion instruments, typically cymbals, which are set up on stands to be played by a single player with drumsticks held in both hands and the feet operating pedals that control the hi-hat cymbal and the beater for the bass drum.
/m/02hnl.comments_JP: Many drum kits are drum machines. Remove this distinction by far?
/m/02hnl.name: Drum kit

/m/02cz_7.description: A form of vocal percussion primarily involving the art of mimicking drum machines using one's mouth, lips, tongue, and voice.
/m/02cz_7.name: Beatboxing

/m/05kms.description: The sounds of straight-bored double-reed woodwind instruments.
/m/05kms.name: Oboe

/m/0dv5r.description: Sounds of mechanical or electronic instruments that employ optics to record or capture images.
/m/0dv5r.name: Camera

/m/0dwtp.description: Sounds of a percussion instrument composed of a set of tuned metal plates or tubes laid out like the keyboard of a piano.
/m/0dwtp.name: Glockenspiel

/m/02qmj0d.description: The sound of a group of string instruments typically present in a standard classical orchestra.
/m/02qmj0d.comments_JP: Be careful with midi notes, if we want to remove midi notes filter with tags such as midi-velocity. This class we should be careful with the defenition, because this should be a group!
/m/02qmj0d.name: String section

/m/0d31p.description: The sound of a device that uses an air pump to create a partial vacuum to suck up dust and dirt, usually from floors and other surfaces such as upholstery and draperies.
/m/0d31p.name: Vacuum cleaner

/m/02dgv.description: Sounds of a moving structure used to open or close an entrance to an enclosed space such as a building or vehicle.
/m/02dgv.name: Door

/m/03j1ly.description: The sound of any vehicle that is designated and authorized to respond to an emergency. Since emergency vehicles often need to travel at high speeds, they are frequently fitted with audible sirens to warn other motorists to give way.
/m/03j1ly.name: Emergency vehicle

/m/07pzfmf.description: An irregular sequence of sharp sounds, as from sudden vaporization of liquids trapped in a burning solid, or from a collection of snapping noises.
/m/07pzfmf.name: Crackle

/m/01dwxx.description: Sounds associated with the family of seabirds often encountered in coastal regions.
/m/01dwxx.name: Gull, seagull

/m/02lkt.description: A large set of predominantly popular and dance genres in which synthesizers and other electronic instruments are the primary sources of sound.
/m/02lkt.name: Electronic music

/m/03_d0.description: A music genre that originated from African American communities of New Orleans during the late 19th and early 20th centuries in the form of independent traditional and popular musical styles, all linked by the common bonds of African American and European American musical parentage with a performance orientation.
/m/03_d0.name: Jazz

/m/07r5c2p.description: The relatively harsh sound made by corvine birds.
/m/07r5c2p.name: Caw

/m/01v1d8.description: Sounds suggesting the use of an electronic musical instrument that uses recordings of sounds loaded or recorded into it by the user, then played back by means of the sampler program itself, a keyboard, sequencer, or another triggering device.
/m/01v1d8.comments_JP: Very difficult to find a song which is generated with a sampler. Remove class.
/m/01v1d8.name: Sampler

/m/0342h.description: Sounds of a string instrument with between 4 and 18 strings (typically 6) running over a fretboard, typically played by strumming or plucking the strings with the right hand while fretting the strings with the fingers of the left hand.
/m/0342h.name: Guitar

/m/07rpk1c.description: A sharp, vibrating sound, as of a branch whipping back into shape, or a bow after releasing an arrow.  Musical plucked strings are not included.
/m/07rpk1c.name: Twang

/m/01lsmm.description: The sound of hand-operated shearing tools consisting of a pair of metal blades pivoted so that the sharpened edges slide against each other when the handles opposite to the pivot are closed.
/m/01lsmm.name: Scissors

/m/06wzb.description: Sounds caused by  water in the gas phase, which is formed when water boils.
/m/06wzb.name: Steam

/m/01m2v.description: Sounds created by a typewriter-style device which uses an arrangement of buttons or keys controlling switches to enter text or other information into a computer or other electronic device.
/m/01m2v.name: Computer keyboard

/t/dd00028.description: Portmanteau class for categories that describe music according to its functional role. Although the genre and instrumentation of examples of each of these classes may vary widely, a listener will be able to recognize that the music is being used for a common specific purpose as stated in each class definition.
/t/dd00028.comments_JP: 8/10 classes have the review tag. I propose blacklisting most of them, because some of them might be very useful.
/t/dd00028.name: Music role

/m/07pp_mv.description: The sound of an automatic signal warning of danger.
/m/07pp_mv.name: Alarm

/m/02k_mr.description: A sustained sound produced by multiple, rapid strikes between drum sticks and drum, made possible by bouncing alternating sticks off the head to produce a temporally dense sequence.
/m/02k_mr.name: Drum roll

/m/05kq4.description: Sounds of the body of saline water that composes much of Earth's surface.
/m/05kq4.comments_XF: Should we include sea, liake, river ?
/m/05kq4.name: Ocean

/m/07rc7d9.description: Dog communication sound that is more tonal and less abrupt than a classic bark.
/m/07rc7d9.name: Bow-wow

/m/0llzx.description: Sounds of a machine used to stitch fabric and other materials together with thread.
/m/0llzx.name: Sewing machine

/m/09dsr.description: A linear succession of musical tones that the listener perceives as a single entity; a combination of pitch and rhythm, also known as a tune, voice, or line.
/m/09dsr.name: Melody

/m/01xq0k1.description: Sounds associated with the most common type of large domesticated ungulates.
/m/01xq0k1.name: Cattle, bovinae

/m/02zsn.description: Speech uttered by an adult female human.
/m/02zsn.name: Female speech, woman speaking

/m/07rjzl8.description: The sound of a door or other hinged cover being closed violently.
/m/07rjzl8.name: Slam

/m/06xkwv.description: A low, continuous tone caused by electromagnetic interference from the alternating current of the mains electricity. The fundamental frequency of this sound is usually 50 Hz or 60 Hz, depending on the local power-line frequency.
/m/06xkwv.name: Mains hum

/m/0199g.description: Sounds of a human-powered, pedal-driven vehicle, having two wheels attached to a frame, one behind the other.
/m/0199g.name: Bicycle

/m/07plct2.description: The sound of a brittle, rigid structure breaking into small pieces or catastrophically deforming.
/m/07plct2.name: Crushing

/m/079vc8.description: A two-toned whistle commonly made to show high interest or approval of something or someone (typically sexual).
/m/079vc8.name: Wolf-whistling

/t/dd00029.description: Music specifically used or performed at birthday celebrations.
/t/dd00029.name: Birthday music

/m/03r5q_.description: A short song or tune used in advertising and for other commercial uses. The jingle contains one or more hooks that explicitly promote the product or service being advertised.
/m/03r5q_.name: Jingle (music)

/m/0z9c.description: Group or solo singing without instrumental accompaniment.
/m/0z9c.name: A capella

/m/09hlz4.description: Sounds generated by the movement of air through the respiratory system (nose, mouth, trachea, and lungs).
/m/09hlz4.name: Respiratory sounds

/m/07rknqz.description: The sound of a vehicle sliding on a road surface as a consequence of its wheels losing sufficient frictional contact.
/m/07rknqz.name: Skidding

/m/07p_0gm.description: A dull, continunous sound with a strong rhythmic modulation.
/m/07p_0gm.name: Throbbing

/m/03qtq.description: The sound of a mating pair of small cymbals mounted atop one-another on a stand, the bottom fixed and the top activated up and down by a foot pedal. The rate of decay of the sound is changed between a shimmering and sharp effect by pressing on the pedal.
/m/03qtq.name: Hi-hat

/m/0y4f8.description: Music performed by one or more singers, with or without instrumental accompaniment, in which singing provides the main focus of the piece.
/m/0y4f8.name: Vocal music

/m/0316dw.description: The sound of writing or inputting text by pressing keys on a typewriter, computer keyboard, cell phone, or calculator.
/m/0316dw.name: Typing

/m/07rdhzs.description: The sound of a partially rigid object forcefully striking another object, which may be preceded by the sound of the rapid, driven motion of one object (as of a baseball bat hitting a ball).
/m/07rdhzs.name: Whack, thwack

/m/07p7b8y.description: The sound of a container being filled with liquid.
/m/07p7b8y.name: Fill (with liquid)

/m/0174nj.description: A sound which appears to come from a gramophone or vinyl record disc being played on a turntable.
/m/0174nj.name: Gramophone record

/t/dd00092.description: The noise produced when a strong air current passes over a microphone, causing large amplitude local turbulence, normally recorded as mechanical clipping as the microphone element exceeds its limits of linearity.
/t/dd00092.name: Wind noise (microphone)

/m/0fjy1.description: Sounds of an uncontrolled fire in an area of combustible vegetation that occurs in the countryside.
/m/0fjy1.name: Wildfire

/m/028sqc.description: Musical styles originating from a large number of Asian countries located in Central, Southern, and East Asia.
/m/028sqc.name: Music of Asia

/t/dd00065.description: The sound of a small engine such as a toy car, sewing machine, or moped.
/t/dd00065.comments_EF: dont know where to put washing-machine
/t/dd00065.name: Light engine (high frequency)

/m/03w6d1.description: A harmonic or monophonic effect or accompaniment where a note or chord is continuously sounded throughout most or all of a musical piece.
/m/03w6d1.name: Drone

/m/03m9d0z.description: Sounds caused by the large-scale flow of gases, especially the air flowing over the surface of the Earth. Long-duration winds have various names associated with their average strength, such as breeze, gale, storm, and hurricane.
/m/03m9d0z.name: Wind

/m/025cbm.description: Sounds of an electrically-amplified keyboard instrument with a distinctive bright staccato sound, popular in funk, jazz-funk, rock, and soul songs.
/m/025cbm.name: Clavinet

/m/018w8.description: The sound of a basketball bouncing on a hard surface, such as a basketball court.
/m/018w8.name: Basketball bounce

/m/07qrkrw.description: The classic tonal communication sound made by cats.
/m/07qrkrw.name: Meow

/m/04zc0.description: A sound which appears to come from a compressed digital file using the MP3 format, discernible by containing nearly imperceptible compression artifacts.
/m/04zc0.name: MP3

/m/01qbl.description: The sound of a percussion instrument consisting of thin, normally round plates of various alloys. They may be used in pairs, struck together, or as single cymbals struck with sticks.
/m/01qbl.name: Cymbal

/m/01sb50.description: The low buzz emitted by the vibrotactile actuator used to provide "silent alarms" on mobile phones and other devices.
/m/01sb50.name: Cellphone buzz, vibrating alert

/m/07r_80w.description: The loud raucous cry of an owl.
/m/07r_80w.name: Hoot

/m/0h2mp.description: Sounds associated with these insects of the order Diptera, which use only a single pair of wings to fly.
/m/0h2mp.name: Fly, housefly

/m/07q0yl5.description: The sound of a single, hard exhalation through the nose.
/m/07q0yl5.name: Snort

/m/02y_763.description: The sound of a type of door which opens horizontally by sliding, usually parallel to a wall.
/m/02y_763.name: Sliding door

/t/dd00134.description: The sound of a motorized vehicle as it passes by a listener close to the vehicle's path. The sound may include engine and tire noise and will typically involve a clear build-up and/or decay of intensity as the vehicle approaches and retreats, as well as possible Doppler shift.
/t/dd00134.name: Car passing by

/m/07r67yg.description: A multi-tone chime made by a doorbell.
/m/07r67yg.name: Ding-dong

/m/078jl.description: Sounds associated with the elongated, legless, carnivorous reptiles of the suborder Serpentes.
/m/078jl.name: Snake

/m/07y_7.description: The sound of a wooden string instrument, typically with four strings tuned in perfect fifths, that is most commonly played by drawing a bow across its strings, though it can also be played by plucking the strings.
/m/07y_7.comments_JP: when presenting this class, show parents and childs for annotation
/m/07y_7.name: Violin, fiddle

/m/05jcn.description: A pitched sound forming the "atom" of much written music.
/m/05jcn.comments_JP: Add packs from Oriol, and other things we already know are good.
/m/05jcn.name: Musical note

/m/07rrlb6.description: The sound of a liquid colliding with a hard surface.
/m/07rrlb6.name: Splash, splatter

/m/0f25s6.description: Other sound deliberately made by cats to communicate with other animals.
/m/0f25s6.name: Cat communication

/m/0164x2.description: Music whose style or form clearly indicates African origin or primarily African influence. Given the vastness of the continent, this covers many distinct musical traditions. Sub-Saharan African music frequently relies on percussion instruments including xylophones, drums, and tone-producing instruments such as the mbira or "thumb piano."
/m/0164x2.name: Music of Africa

/m/07qw_06.description: A weak or soft emotional vocalization, possibly indicating pain, sadness, or pleasure.
/m/07qw_06.name: Wail, moan

/m/0_ksk.description: Sounds of tools that employ a power source other than the manual labor used with hand tools. The most common types of power tools use electric motors.
comments_EF: difficult to expand. few results. consider adding industrial, machine, motor, engine
/m/0_ksk.name: Power tool

/m/059j3w.description: Sounds produced by natural sources in their normal soundscape, excluding animal and human sounds.
/m/059j3w.name: Natural sounds

/m/06mb1.description: The sound of droplets of liquid water that have condensed from atmospheric water vapor and then fallen under gravity.
/m/06mb1.name: Rain

/m/07qh7jl.description: A high-pitched noise with a perceptible variation in pitch as a result of pressure being shifted or applied on a surface, most commonly on wood.
/m/07qh7jl.name: Creak

/m/0dl83.description: Sounds of a shafted projectile that is shot with a bow.
/m/0dl83.name: Arrow

/m/0bxl5.description: Sounds of an electric piano invented by Harold Rhodes in which the hammers strike thin metal tines, which are then amplified via an electromagnetic pickup.
/m/0bxl5.name: Rhodes piano

/m/07pjjrj.description: The sound of a rigid structure violently breaking into many pieces.
/m/07pjjrj.name: Smash, crash

/m/02ccj9.description: A dance-oriented music genre popular throughout Latin America which began as a courtship dance practiced among the African population on the Caribbean coasts of Colombia and Panama but later mixed with Amerindian and European instruments, steps, and musical characteristics.
/m/02ccj9.name: Cumbia

/m/0gg8l.description: A form of American roots music from the Appalachias with mixed roots in Irish, Scottish, Welsh, and English traditional music, later influenced by the music of African-Americans through incorporation of jazz elements.
/m/0gg8l.name: Bluegrass

/m/07qyrcz.description: The sound of a small object dropping into a liquid without a splash.
/m/07qyrcz.name: Plop

/m/0b9m1.description: A sine tone whose frequency is an integer multiple of some fundamental tone.
/m/0b9m1.name: Harmonic

/m/07svc2k.description: The characteristic sound made by a turkey cock.
/m/07svc2k.name: Gobble

/m/02sgy.description: Sounds of a guitar that uses a pickup to convert the vibration of its strings (which are typically made of metal, and which occurs when a guitarist strums, plucks, or fingerpicks the strings) into electrical impulses, which are then amplified and converted to sound.
/m/02sgy.name: Electric guitar

/m/0c3f7m.description: Sounds of a system designed to warn people when smoke, fire, carbon monoxide or other emergencies are present. Alarms can be either motorized bells or wall-mountable sounders or horns.
/m/0c3f7m.name: Fire alarm

/m/05mxj0q.description: Sounds associated with self-adhesive tape from wide rolls used to seal cardboard boxes and other temporary attachments. Specifically includes the distinctive noise of the tape being dispensed from a roll.
/m/05mxj0q.name: Packing tape, duct tape

/m/04zmvq.description: The sound of an audible signaling device on a steam locomotive used to warn that the train is approaching, and to communicate with rail workers.
/m/04zmvq.name: Train whistle

/t/dd000138.description: Short-duration sounds composed of strong harmonics with a distinct pitch.
/t/dd000138.name: Brief tone

/m/0n8zsc8.description: A music genre that originated from hip hop in the early 1990s in the Southern United States, typified by its aggressive lyrical content and sound.
/m/0n8zsc8.comments_JP: Too specific class. No clear examples. Remove.
/m/0n8zsc8.name: Trap music

/m/0_1c.description: The sound of large military weapons built to fire munitions far beyond the range and power of infantry's small arms.
/m/0_1c.name: Artillery fire

/m/0dbvp.description: Sounds associated with this species of larger waterfowl.
/m/0dbvp.name: Goose

/m/01jnbd.description: A sound which is a delayed and attenuated repetition of an earlier sound, for example because the sound wave has been reflected back from a distant, planar surface. To be perceived as an echo, the repetion must be delayed by around 100 milliseconds or more.
/m/01jnbd.name: Echo

/m/07qv_x_.description: Walk while dragging the feet, often indicating impaired mobility.
/m/07qv_x_.name: Shuffle

/m/016622.description: Sounds of tuned percussion instruments consisting of a metal tube, tuned by altering its length in the range C4-F5.
/m/016622.name: Tubular bells

/m/07r_25d.description: The sound made by a pigeon or dove.
/m/07r_25d.name: Coo

/m/07qnq_y.description: A heavy dull sound, as made by impact of heavy objects with a relatively soft point of contact.
/m/07qnq_y.name: Thump, thud

/m/07pqc89.description: The sound of a liquid flowing slowly in an unsteady stream or drops.
/m/07pqc89.name: Trickle, dribble

/m/02p3nc.description: A strong, involuntary contraction of the diaphragm that may repeat several times per minute.
/m/02p3nc.name: Hiccup

/m/016cjb.description: A genre of Christian music usually featuring dominant vocals with Christian lyrics. Gospel music is rooted in the black oral tradition, in which hymns and sacred songs were repeated in call and response fashion, with hand clapping and foot stomping as rhythmic accompaniment.
/m/016cjb.comments_JP: Very noisy class, not that much examples.
/m/016cjb.name: Gospel music

/m/0190y4.description: A genre of music that grew out of reggae, consisting predominantly of instrumental remixes of existing recordings achieved by significantly manipulating and reshaping the recordings, usually by removing the vocals from an existing music piece, and emphasizing the drum and bass parts.
/m/0190y4.name: Dub

/m/0j45pbj.description: Sounds of melodic percussion instruments consisting of an array of elements, one for each note, played with mallets.
/m/0j45pbj.name: Mallet percussion

/m/01lyv.description: A genre of United States popular music with origins in folk, Blues and Western music, often consisting of ballads and dance tunes with generally simple forms and harmonies accompanied by mostly string instruments such as banjos, electric and acoustic guitars, dobros, and fiddles as well as harmonicas.
/m/01lyv.name: Country

/m/0gywn.description: A popular music genre that combines elements of African-American gospel music, rhythm and blues and jazz.
/m/0gywn.name: Soul music

/m/01vj9c.description: Sounds of musical instruments that produce tones in the low-pitched range, typically providing a tonic root in a musical ensemble.
/m/01vj9c.comments_JP: Remove this one, is very difficult
/m/01vj9c.name: Bass (instrument role)

/m/09d5_.description: Sounds associated with the mostly solitary and nocturnal carnivorous birds from the order Strigiformes.
/m/09d5_.name: Owl

/m/02bxd.description: The sound of an Indigenous Australian wind instrument, usually cylindrical or conical, measuring anywhere from 1 to 3 m long.
/m/02bxd.name: Didgeridoo

/m/04k94.description: Sounds of a fluid that conforms to the shape of its container but retains a constant volume independent of pressure.
/m/04k94.name: Liquid

/m/04gxbd.description: The sound of automobile windows being raised and lowered by a built-in electric motor, controlled by a button or switch.
/m/04gxbd.name: Power windows, electric windows

/m/06_fw.description: Sounds of a type of sports equipment consisting of a board mounted on two pairs of wheels. A skateboard is typically propelled by pushing with one foot while the other remains on the board, or by simply standing on the deck while on a downward slope and allowing gravity to propel the board and rider.
/m/06_fw.name: Skateboard

/m/025td0t.description: Styles of music or soundscapes primarily intended to be listened to passively and not meant to be the main focus of an audience.
/m/025td0t.comments_JP: It seems to be a lot of background sounds in FS. Maybe is a too broad class.
/m/025td0t.name: Background music

/m/07s2xch.description: An utterance expressing pain or disapproval. Specifically refers to humans.
/m/07s2xch.comments_XF: get other kind of sounds (orgasm, monster groan)
/m/07s2xch.name: Groan

/m/03qtwd.description: The sound of a large group of people gathered together.
/m/03qtwd.name: Crowd

/m/01v_m0.description: A continuous, pure tone of fixed pitch and amplitude.
/m/01v_m0.name: Sine wave

/m/07pp8cl.description: The sound of a physical or synthesized electric bell ringing to signal an incoming telephone call.
/m/07pp8cl.name: Telephone bell ringing

/m/023pjk.description: The sounds of hand implements such as knife, fork, and spoon, that are typically made of steel and are used in preparing, serving, and eating food in the Western world.
/m/023pjk.name: Cutlery, silverware

/m/0dwsp.description: Sounds of a percussion instrument consisting of a set of wooden bars struck with mallets to produce musical tones. Resonators suspended underneath the bars may amplify their sound.
/m/0dwsp.name: Marimba, xylophone

/m/01jwx6.description: The general class of sounds caused by a periodic mechanical oscillation.
/m/01jwx6.name: Vibration

/m/01xqw.description: The sound of a larger, lower-pitched bowed string instrument with four strings tuned in perfect fifths, usually C2, G2, D3, and A3.
/m/01xqw.name: Cello

/m/05w3f.description: A style of rock music influenced by psychedelic culture and attempts to replicate and enhance the mind-altering experiences of psychedelic drugs, most notably LSD. It often uses new recording techniques and effects and sometimes draws on sources such as the ragas and drones of Indian music.
/m/05w3f.name: Psychedelic rock

/m/07qfgpx.description: An irregular pattern of short metallic sounds, especially from small metal objects such as keys or coins shaking against each other.
/m/07qfgpx.name: Jingle, tinkle

/m/0463cq4.description: Sound associated with the shedding of tears in response to an emotional state, arising from slow but erratic inhalation, occasional instances of breath holding and muscular tremor.
/m/0463cq4.name: Crying, sobbing

/m/09f96.description: Sounds associated with these small, midge-like flies whose tube-like mouth parts pierce the hosts' skin to consume blood.
/m/09f96.name: Mosquito

/m/06hps.description: Sounds associated with the small mammals of the order Rodentia, found in vast numbers on all continents except Antarctica.
/m/06hps.name: Rodents, rats, mice

/m/04szw.description: Sounds specifically associated with instruments created, adapted or otherwise used to make musical sounds.
/m/04szw.name: Musical instrument

/m/014zdl.description: The sound of a rapid increase in volume and release of energy in an extreme manner, usually with the generation of high temperatures and the release of gases.
/m/014zdl.name: Explosion

/t/dd00093.description: A class for sounds that convey the spatiality of the recording.
/t/dd00093.name: Acoustic environment

/t/dd00031.description: Music that evokes or conveys feelings of happiness.
/t/dd00031.name: Happy music

/m/0l14j_.description: The sound of an aerophone or reedless wind instrument that produces its sound from the flow of air across an opening.
/m/0l14j_.name: Flute

/m/01c3q.description: The sound of the low-pitched double-reed woodwind instrument with a folded bore.
/m/01c3q.name: Bassoon

/m/01b7fy.description: A sound that appears to have been produced by headphones.
/m/01b7fy.name: Headphones

/m/01h82_.description: A metallic "pinging" sound caused by a malfunctioning spark-ignited internal combustion engine. Engine knocking indicates that the combustion of the air/fuel mixture in the cylinder is occurring at the wrong point in the piston's stroke.
/m/01h82_.name: Engine knocking

/m/03xq_f.description: Sounds of an electronic keyboard instrument designed to imitate the sound of the pipe organ.
/m/03xq_f.name: Electronic organ

/m/0d8_n.description: The sound of playing a stringed instrument that is usually bowed (such as a violin) by plucking the strings with the fingers.
/m/0d8_n.name: Pizzicato

/m/07q0h5t.description: Communicative vocalization of sheep and goats.
/m/07q0h5t.name: Bleat

/m/02fs_r.description: A short, single tone, generally made by a computer or other machine and typically high-pitched.
/m/02fs_r.name: Beep, bleep

/m/09b5t.description: Sounds of the very common and widespread domesticated fowl, raised for its eggs and meat.
/m/09b5t.name: Chicken, rooster

/m/022dgg.description: A music genre that emerged in South Africa, during the 1990s. It is a variant of house music featuring the use of African sounds and samples.
/m/022dgg.name: Kwaito

/m/07p9k1k.description: The sound of many small bubbles bursting, most often caused by fat vaporizing as it is heated.
/m/07p9k1k.name: Sizzle

/m/068zj.description: Sounds associated with the highly intelligent, very common, domesticated relative of the boar.
/m/068zj.name: Pig

/m/012xff.description: Sounds of an instrument used to clean the teeth and gums consisting of a head of tightly clustered bristles mounted on a handle.
/m/012xff.name: Toothbrush

/m/01kcd.description: The sound of a musical instrument that produces sound by vibration of air in a tubular resonator in sympathy with the vibration of the player's lips.
/m/01kcd.name: Brass instrument

/m/07q5rw0.description: The characteristic communication sound made by a horse.
/m/07q5rw0.name: Neigh, whinny

/m/0m0jc.description: An umbrella term that encompasses a broad group of electronic-based styles such as techno, house, ambient, drum and bass, jungle, and industrial dance, among others.
/m/0m0jc.name: Electronica

/m/01d3sd.description: The sound resulting from obstructed respiratory airways during breathing while sleeping.
/m/01d3sd.name: Snoring

/m/01yg9g.description: The sound of a machine utilizing one or more revolving blades to cut grass, powered by an electric motor, a small internal combustion engine, or by a human pushing the machine.
/m/01yg9g.name: Lawn mower

/m/02x8m.description: A music genre that originated in the 1960s when African American musicians created a rhythmic, danceable new form of music that de-emphasized melody and chord progressions to bring a strong rhythmic groove of a bass line and drum part to the foreground.
/m/02x8m.name: Funk

/m/05r5wn.description: The sound of an instrument that produces a sound when shaken, usually consisting of a closed rigid shell containing numerous small particles that strike the shell when shaken.
/m/05r5wn.name: Rattle (instrument)

/m/04rlf.description: Music is an art form and cultural activity whose medium is sound and silence. The common elements of music are pitch, rhythm, dynamics, and the sonic qualities of timbre and texture.
/m/04rlf.name: Music

/m/05lls.description: An art form in which singers and musicians perform a dramatic work combining text and musical score, usually in a theatrical setting.
/m/05lls.name: Opera

/m/07qlf79.description: The sound of a liquid being transferred in a scatter or jet of droplets.
/m/07qlf79.name: Spray

/m/07prgkl.description: The sound of liquid being transferred in a steady stream.
/m/07prgkl.name: Pour

/g/11b630rrvh.description: The high-pitched sound of a whistle attached to the spout of an appliance for boiling water.  When the water boils, steam is forced through the whistle, alerting users that boiling is complete.
/g/11b630rrvh.name: Kettle whistle

/m/02_41.description: Sounds resulting from  the rapid oxidation of a material in the exothermic chemical process of combustion, releasing heat, light, and various reaction products.
/m/02_41.name: Fire

/m/0g293.description: Music originating from Latin America which encompasses a wide variety of styles, including son, rumba, salsa, merengue, tango, samba, and bossa nova.
/m/0g293.name: Music of Latin America

/m/0140xf.description: A variety of genres of music normally performed or heard around the Christmas season.
/m/0140xf.name: Christmas music

/m/0jbk.description: All sound produced by the bodies and actions of nonhuman animals.
/m/0jbk.name: Animal

/m/03fwl.description: Sounds of the medium-sized domesticated bovidae.
/m/03fwl.name: Goat

/m/07q6cd_.description: A short, high-pitched noise without a sharp attack.
/m/07q6cd_.name: Squeak
