/m/07r4gkf.description: A quick succession of light rapid sounds, usually suggesting the locomotion of small animals.
/m/07r4gkf.name: Patter

/m/014yck.description: The sound of the part of an aircraft that generates mechanical power. Aircraft engines are almost always lightweight piston engines, gas turbines, or, in small multicopter UAVs, electric motors.
/m/014yck.name: Aircraft engine

/m/07pws3f.comments_XF: Does this include firework for example?
/m/07pws3f.name: Bang

/m/04v5dt.description: Vocal display of displeasure for someone or something, generally an entertainer, by loudly yelling "boo!" or making other noises of disparagement.
/m/04v5dt.name: Booing

/m/04rzd.description: Sounds of an instrument in the lute family, commonly with 4 courses of doubled metal strings, usually plucked with a plectrum or "pick".
/m/04rzd.name: Mandolin

/t/dd00005.description: Singing produced by a young human whose voice has not yet reached its adult state.
/t/dd00005.name: Child singing

/t/dd00048.description: The high-pitched tones caused by steel train wheels rubbing against rails, for instance when traversing a tight bend or when braking.
/t/dd00048.name: Train wheels squealing

/m/05r6t.description: A rock music genre that developed between 1974 and 1976 typically composed of short or fast-paced songs, with hard-edged melodies and singing styles, stripped-down instrumentation, and often political, anti-establishment lyrics.
/m/05r6t.name: Punk rock

/t/dd00012.description: Sounds produced by groups of humans rather than individuals.
/t/dd00012.comments_XF: Idea of group of humans. Need plural form? (no stem)
/t/dd00012.name: Human group actions

/m/0dwt5.description: Sounds of a tuned mallet percussion instrument similar to a xylophone or glockenspiel with the addition a motor-driven valve on each resonator that produce a tremolo or vibrato effect.
/m/0dwt5.name: Vibraphone

/m/09l8g.description: The human voice consists of sound made by a human being using the vocal folds for talking, singing, laughing, crying, screaming, etc. The human voice is specifically a part of human sound production in which the vocal folds are the primary sound source.
/m/09l8g.name: Human voice

/t/dd00139.description: The sound of a rapid exhale through a horse's nose.
/t/dd00139.name: Snort (horse)

/m/081rb.description: The sound of inscribing signs and symbols, most often by using a purpose-made hand-held device, such as a pen or pencil, directly upon paper or similar media.
/m/081rb.name: Writing

/m/06ncr.description: The sound of a woodwind instrument made of brass and played with a single-reed mouthpiece similar to that of the clarinet.
/m/06ncr.name: Saxophone

/m/0bt9lr.description: Any sounds coming from the familiar domesticated canid which has been selectively bred over millennia for companionship, protection, as well as for superior sensory capabilities, and other useful behaviors.
/m/0bt9lr.name: Dog

/m/0cmf2.description: Sounds of an aircraft capable of flight using wings that generate lift caused by the vehicle's forward airspeed and the shape of the wings.
/m/0cmf2.comments_JP: May be good to add airport category in the ASO
/m/0cmf2.name: Fixed-wing aircraft, airplane

/m/07qv4k0.description: The sound of a hard edge dragging across a surface.
/m/07qv4k0.name: Scrape

/m/01sm1g.description: The sound of a small slit drum made from a single piece of wood, making a very short, clean sound.
/m/01sm1g.name: Wood block

/m/09t49.description: The sound of dried leaves rubbing against one another in respondse to being moved by the wind or another cause.
/m/09t49.name: Rustling leaves

/m/07rkbfh.description: The combined sound of casual speech by many people in individual simultaneous conversations.
/m/07rkbfh.name: Chatter

/m/08p9q4.description: The audible feedback on a telecommunications channel that allows the speaker to know that the channel is operational.
/m/08p9q4.name: Sidetone

/m/01b_21.description: A sudden and often repetitively occurring reflex which consists of an inhalation, a forced exhalation against a closed glottis, and a violent release of air following opening of the glottis.
/m/01b_21.name: Cough

/m/0f8s22.description: The sound of a musical instrument consisting of multiple tuned bells, usually rung by an automated mechanism to produce a short, characteristic tone or melody.
/m/0f8s22.name: Chime

/m/07q2z82.description: The sound made by the engine of a vehicle undergoing acceleration, usually involving an increase in loudness and a rising pitch.
/m/07q2z82.name: Accelerating, revving, vroom

/m/07s0s5r.description: The sound of playing a guitar by dragging a finger or plectrum over multiple strings near-simultaneously.
/m/07s0s5r.name: Strum

/m/07sq110.description: Very loud and abrupt laughter that encompasses much of the body.
/m/07sq110.name: Belly laugh

/m/02fsn.description: The sound of a large, bowed string instrument, the lowest-pitched in a standard symphony orchestra, with strings usually tuned to E1, A1, D2, and G2.
/m/02fsn.name: Double bass

/m/0kpv1t.description: Portmanteau class holding categories that represent styles or classifications of music, useful in identifying and organizing similar musical artists or recordings.
/m/0kpv1t.comments_JP: 27/145 have the review tag. Overall, genre is a very broad thing that in freesound is illdefined. In most cases we get isolated examples, or parts of the thing because freesound is that way
/m/0kpv1t.name: Music genre

/m/022c7z.description: The basic unit of musical time -- the pulse -- of the mensural level. The beat is often defined as the rhythm listeners would tap their toes to when listening to a piece of music.
/m/022c7z.name: Beat

/m/07pyy8b.description: Fast and noisy breathing, often associated with physical exertion.
/m/07pyy8b.name: Pant

/m/01wy6.description: The sound of a woodwind instrument consisting of a single-reed mouthpiece, a straight cylindrical tube with an almost cylindrical bore, and a flared bell.
/m/01wy6.name: Clarinet

/m/07rgkc5.description: A crackling or hissing noise caused by electrical interference.
/m/07rgkc5.name: Static

/m/06rqw.description: A music genre that originated in Jamaica in the late 1950s, combining elements of Caribbean mento and calypso with American jazz and rhythm and blues. It is characterized by a walking bass line accented with rhythms on the off-beat.
/m/06rqw.name: Ska

/m/02cjck.description: Music often written specifically for a radio program, television program, video game, or movie, and usually played during the intro, opening credits, and/or ending credits.
/m/02cjck.name: Theme music

/m/02p01q.description: Sounds of a common wood- and metal-working tool used to remove fine amounts of material from a workpiece.
/m/02p01q.name: Filing (rasp)

/m/01c194.description: A melodic sacred utterance believed to have spiritual powers.
/m/01c194.name: Mantra

/m/07srf8z.description: The sound made by a hound on the scent.
/m/07srf8z.name: Bay

/m/07r4k75.description: A short low gruff noise, resembling the sound made by animals such as pigs. Specifically refers to humans.
/m/07r4k75.name: Grunt

/m/04xp5v.description: A sound generated within the inner ear, generally understood to result from positive feedback in the highly-sensitive ear mechanism.
/m/04xp5v.comments_XF: Don't find any of these in Freesound
/m/04xp5v.name: Otoacoustic emission

/m/07rjwbb.description: A fricative sound, such as from a cat giving warning, or an audience indicating disapproval.
/m/07rjwbb.name: Hiss

/m/02rtxlg.description: Unvoiced speech, usually intended to be quieter to avoid causing disturbance or being overheard.
/m/02rtxlg.name: Whispering

/t/dd00108.description: A predominantly low-frequency impact noise that starts with a cleaner, high-frequency click, suggesting the contact of rigid surfaces (as of a car door closing).
/t/dd00108.name: Clunk

/m/0l14t7.description: The sound of a type of bell that sits with the bottom surface resting, allowing the rim to vibrate to produce sound.
/m/0l14t7.name: Singing bowl

/m/0dq0md.description: Hindi film songs featured in Bollywood films. Bollywood songs, along with dance, are a characteristic motif of Hindi cinema which gives it enduring popular appeal, cultural value, and context.
/m/0dq0md.name: Music of Bollywood

/m/046dlr.description: Sounds made by a clock that is designed to make an audible signal at a specific time. The primary use of alarm clocks is to awaken people from their night's sleep.
/m/046dlr.name: Alarm clock

/m/0cdnk.description: Sounds associated with the larger and more ferocious wild relatives of cats.
/m/0cdnk.name: Roaring cats (lions, tigers)

/m/021wwz.description: The low-pitched instrumental part or line played by a rhythm section instrument such as the electric bass, double bass, cello, tuba, or keyboard in many forms of popular and other music.
/m/021wwz.name: Bassline

/m/01j3sz.description: The sound of rhythmical contractions of the diaphragm in response to stimuli such as tickling, or from humorous stories or thoughts.
/m/01j3sz.name: Laughter

/m/05xp3j.description: A rhythmic pattern establishing the meter and groove through the pulse and subdivision, played on drum kits and other percussion instruments.
/m/05xp3j.name: Drum beat

/m/034srq.description: Sounds caused by the surface waves that occur on the free surface of oceans, seas, lakes, rivers, etc., resulting from the wind blowing over the surface.
/m/034srq.name: Waves, surf

/t/dd00128.description: Sounds that appear to have been recorded outdoors in a human-constructed environment.
/t/dd00128.name: Outside, urban or manmade

/m/093_4n.description: Sounds present alongside a sound of interest but typically weaker in energy and generally not of interest.
/m/093_4n.name: Background noise

/m/0bpl036.description: Sounds resulting from human body actions involved in changing location.
/m/0bpl036.name: Human locomotion

/m/028v0c.description: The absence of audible sound or presence of sounds of very low intensity.
/m/028v0c.name: Silence

/m/01z7dr.description: The soundtrack that accompanies video games. Early video game music was once limited to simple melodies of early sound synthesizer technology; with advances in technology, video game music has now grown to include the same breadth and complexity associated with television and movie soundtracks.
/m/01z7dr.comments_JP: I am not sure if music role is a relevant aspect, because they are very broad classes.
/m/01z7dr.name: Video game music

/m/02c8p.description: The sound of a telephony signaling system where short combinations of tones within the frequency range of human speech are used to transmit individual digits.
/m/02c8p.name: Telephone dialing, DTMF

/m/0b128.description: The use of simultaneous pitches or chords. Harmony is often said to refer to the "vertical" aspect of music, as distinguished from melodic line, or the "horizontal" aspect.
/m/0b128.comments_JP: It is hard to map this concept. Also difficult to search at FS.
/m/0b128.name: Harmony

/t/dd00127.description: Sounds that appear to have been recorded in a public space such as store, restaurant, or travel terminus, often characterized by both reverberation and continuous background noise.
/t/dd00127.name: Inside, public space

/m/0642b4.description: The sound of the door to a storage cabinet being opened or closed.
/m/0642b4.name: Cupboard open or close

/m/09xqv.description: Sounds associated with these relatives of grasshoppers characterized by enlarged hind legs, providing power for jumping. Crickets are mainly nocturnal, and are best known for the loud, persistent, chirping song of males trying to attract females.
/m/09xqv.name: Cricket

/m/02rlv9.description: Sounds of a boat which is powered by an inboard or outboard engine.
/m/02rlv9.name: Motorboat, speedboat

/m/0c2wf.description: Sounds of a mechanical or electromechanical machine for printing characters by means of keyboard-operated types striking a ribbon to transfer ink or carbon impressions onto paper.
/m/0c2wf.name: Typewriter

/m/0lyf6.description: Air being moved in and out of the lungs in order to sustain life.
/m/0lyf6.name: Breathing

/m/07gxw.description: A form of electronic dance music that emerged in Detroit during the mid-to-late 1980s, resulting from the melding of African American music including with electronic music by artists such as Kraftwerk, Giorgio Moroder, and Yellow Magic Orchestra.
/m/07gxw.name: Techno

/m/0145m.description: A combination of traditional Nigerian music, Ghanaian music, jazz, highlife, funk, and chanted vocals, fused with percussion and vocal styles, popularised in Africa in the 1970s.
/m/0145m.name: Afrobeat

/m/015p6.description: Sounds associated with the large group of flying vertebrates.
/m/015p6.name: Bird

/m/06bxc.description: The sound of "spoken or chanted rhyming lyrics", serving the role of a vocal line in music but with normal speech intonation instead of a melodic line.
/m/06bxc.comments_XF: Precision problem here. Retrieve loops for rap...
/m/06bxc.name: Rapping

/m/0gvgw0.description: Sounds of a vehicle braking system in which compressed air is used to transmit force to the brake pads on the wheels. The pneumatic system makes an abrupt hissing sound when the pressure is released by venting the air.
/m/0gvgw0.name: Air brake

/m/0dl9sf8.description: Forced exhalation through a partially-closed glottis to disrupt built-up mucus, or used as a social signal to draw attention to one's presence.
/m/0dl9sf8.name: Throat clearing

/m/07q8k13.description: A high-pitched noise with a rough quality resembling the cry of a human or other animal.
/m/07q8k13.name: Screech

/m/01hhp3.description: The sound of the long-haired bovid found throughout the Himalaya region of southern Central Asia.
/m/01hhp3.name: Yak

/m/07qn4z3.description: A rapid series of short loud sounds as of small hard items loose inside a container.
comments_EF: it is very broad, as is the definition. dont know how to narrow down
/m/07qn4z3.name: Rattle

/m/01x3z.description: Sounds made by an instrument designed to keep and indicate time.
/m/01x3z.name: Clock

/m/0hg7b.description: Sounds whose origin lie with the microphone used in the recording, rather than the external sound source that was intended to be recorded.
/m/0hg7b.name: Microphone

/m/02v2lh.description: A genre of music intended to create artistic inspiration, relaxation, and optimism used by listeners for yoga, massage, meditation, and reading as a method of stress management or to create a peaceful atmosphere. Includes both electronic and acoustic forms.
/m/02v2lh.name: New-age music

/t/dd00118.description: The sound of the popping of many small bubbles, most often as gas is released from solution, such as in a carbonated beverage.
/t/dd00118.name: Fizz

/m/0155w.description: A genre and musical form developed by African Americans in the United States around the end of the 19th century from African-American work songs and European-American folk music. The blues form, ubiquitous in jazz and rock and roll, is characterized by the call-and-response pattern, the blues scale and specific chord progressions, of which the twelve-bar blues is the most common. Blues shuffles or walking bass reinforce the trance-like rhythm and form a repetitive groove effect.
/m/0155w.name: Blues

/m/01rd7k.description: Sounds associated with the large poultry bird, originally domesticated in the Americas.
/m/01rd7k.name: Turkey

/m/07lnk.description: A genre of electronic dance music that developed in Germany during the 1990s characterized by a tempo between 125 and 150 beats per minute, repeating melodic phrases, and a musical form that distinctly builds tension throughout a track by mixing layers with distinctly foreshadowed build-up and release.
/m/07lnk.name: Trance music

/m/04229.description: The sound of an internal combustion airbreathing engine that generates thrust by discharging a fast-moving jet of gas. Jet aircraft use such engines for long-distance travel.
/m/04229.name: Jet engine

/m/04s8yn.description: Sounds associated with the species of medium-to-large birds, Corvus.
/m/04s8yn.name: Crow

/m/07s34ls.description: A quiet sound of a small object, typically mechanical, in rapid, cyclic motion.
/m/07s34ls.name: Whir

/m/01z5f.description: Sounds associated with the wild relatives of domesticated dogs.
/m/01z5f.name: Canidae, dogs, wolves

/m/02x984l.description: Sounds of a machine used to create air flow via the motion of a rotating arrangement of vanes or blades.
/m/02x984l.name: Mechanical fan

/m/07pn_8q.description: The sound of cutting ingredients into pieces with a knife or similar blade tool.
/m/07pn_8q.name: Chopping (food)

/m/06d_3.description: Sounds associated with wheeled vehicles running on rails (tracks).
/m/06d_3.name: Rail transport

/m/07st89h.description: The soft, low-pitched, and repetitive sound made by chickens.
/m/07st89h.name: Cluck

/m/07rwm0c.description: The sound of fast and rhythmic clicking of machinery, such as keystrokes on a typewriter or steel wheels running on tracks.  Does not include the sound of horses feet (use /m/07rv9rh).
/m/07rwm0c.name: Clickety-clack

/m/07r5v4s.description: The sound of liquid falling in drops.
/m/07r5v4s.name: Drip

/t/dd00027.description: Portmanteau class for descriptions of music sounds that reflect their abstract music-theoretical properties rather than their physical realizations.
/t/dd00027.name: Musical concepts

/m/02pjr4.description: The sound of a kitchen and laboratory appliance used to mix, purée, or emulsify food and other substances, usually by means of metal blades at the base of a container spun rapidly by an electric motor.
/m/02pjr4.name: Blender

/t/dd00030.description: Portmanteau class for music categories that indicate the over emotional affect of music, regardless of genre or instrumentation. These judgments are intrinsically subjective and likely to vary substantially between different musical cultures.
/t/dd00030.comments_JP: 5/7 music moods have review tag. I propose blacklisting most of them, because some of them might be very useful.
/t/dd00030.name: Music mood

/m/02p0sh1.description: Musical forms that have origins many generations into the past, commonly without formal notation or description, commonly familiar to people in a given culture.
/m/02p0sh1.comments_JP: Traditional music in different manners and cultures. Ill-defined class.
/m/02p0sh1.name: Traditional music

/m/0939n_.description: Air from the lungs bubbling through a liquid in the mouth.
/m/0939n_.name: Gargling

/m/03qc9zr.description: A sharp, high-pitched human vocalization; often an instinctive action indicating fear, pain, surprise, joy, anger, etc. Verbal content is absent or overwhelmed, unlike Shout and Yell.
/m/03qc9zr.name: Screaming

/m/0j6m2.description: Sounds of a body of water with a current, confined within a bed and banks.
/m/0j6m2.name: Stream

/m/0hdsk.description: A tone whose frequency increases or decreases with time.
/m/0hdsk.name: Chirp tone

/m/03qjg.description: The sound of a wind instrument played by using the mouth to direct air into or out of one or more holes along a mouthpiece. Behind each hole is a chamber containing at least one reed, producing a specific note or notes.
/m/03qjg.name: Harmonica

/m/01vfsf.description: Sounds specifically associated with an audio amplifier intended for use with an electric guitar, such as overdrive distortion.
/m/01vfsf.name: Guitar amplifier

/t/dd00041.description: Set of sound classes referring to sounds that are immediately understood by listeners as arising from specific objects (rather than being heard more literally as "sounds").
/t/dd00041.comments_XF: Better not to map it. The population will get these
/t/dd00041.name: Sounds of things

/t/dd00126.description: Sounds that appear to have been recorded in a large room or hall, often with clearly perceptible reverberation.
/t/dd00126.name: Inside, large room or hall

/m/04179zz.description: The sound of a tool which imitates the communication calls of waterfowl and is used primarily by hunters to lure prey.
/m/04179zz.name: Duck call (hunting tool)

/m/07ptfmf.description: The sound of moving an implement through a fluid substance.
/m/07ptfmf.name: Stir

/m/07pbtc8.description: The sound of feet or shoes contacting the ground in conventional human locomotion.
/m/07pbtc8.name: Walk, footsteps

/t/dd00032.description: Music that evokes or conveys amusement.
/t/dd00032.name: Funny music

/m/0283d.description: A genre of electronic music that emerged from rave and oldschool jungle scenes in England during the early 1990s characterized by fast, syncopated breakbeats with heavy bass and sub-bass lines, sampled sources, and synthesizers.
/m/0283d.name: Drum and bass

/m/05zppz.description: Speech uttered by an adult male human.
/m/05zppz.name: Male speech, man speaking

/m/0ngt1.description: The sound caused by lightning. Depending on the distance and nature of the lightning, thunder can range from a sharp, loud crack to a long, low rumble.
/m/0ngt1.name: Thunder

/m/03v3yw.description: Sounds made by the mutual collision of small pieces of metal, which are often linked on a ring, used to operate locks.
/m/03v3yw.name: Keys jangling

/t/dd00036.description: Music that evokes or conveys feelings of anger.
/t/dd00036.name: Angry music

/m/0242l.description: The sound of a small, flat, round piece of hard material such as metal or plastic colliding with or bouncing on a hard surface.
/m/0242l.name: Coin (dropping)

/m/023vsd.description: The sounds of a surface being scraped by an abrasive material affixed to sheets of paper or cloth, either to make the surface smoother, remove a layer of material, or sometimes to make the surface rougher.
comments_EF: difficult to narrow down. will probably be noisy
/m/023vsd.name: Sanding

/m/06cqb.description: A music genre that originated in Jamaica in the late 1960s, strongly influenced by traditional mento as well as American jazz and rhythm and blues, instantly recognizable from the counterpoint between the bass and drum downbeat, and the offbeat rhythm section.
/m/06cqb.name: Reggae

/m/096m7z.description: A sound that has no perceptible structure and that typically interferes with the perception of more interesting or important sounds.
/m/096m7z.name: Noise

/m/09ct_.description: Sounds of a type of rotorcraft in which lift and thrust are supplied by rotors. This allows the helicopter to take off and land vertically, to hover, and to fly forward, backward, and laterally.
/m/09ct_.name: Helicopter

/m/085jw.description: Sounds of a family of musical instruments in which a column of air within a resonator is set into vibration by the player blowing into a mouthpiece set at the end of the resonator.
/m/085jw.name: Wind instrument, woodwind instrument

/m/01j4z9.description: The sound of a portable mechanical saw which cuts with a set of teeth attached to a rotating chain. Chainsaws are commonly powered by a small two-stroke internal combustion engine.
/m/01j4z9.name: Chainsaw

/m/02bk07.description: The rhythmic speaking or singing of words or sounds, often primarily on one or two main pitches called reciting tones.
/m/02bk07.name: Chant

/m/01hsr_.description: A convulsive expulsion of air from the lungs through the nose and mouth, usually caused by foreign particles irritating the nasal mucous.
/m/01hsr_.name: Sneeze

/m/0150b9.description: Sounds of the art of ringing a set of (typically large) tuned bells in a controlled manner to produce variations in their sounding order.
/m/0150b9.name: Change ringing (campanology)

/m/07qlwh6.description: Sounds made by a liquid-saturated material being squeezed.
/m/07qlwh6.name: Squish

/m/068hy.description: Sounds of animals kept in close proximity to humans for company, protection, and entertainment.
/m/068hy.name: Domestic animals, pets

/m/0jb2l.description: The sound of a storm characterized by the presence of lightning and its acoustic effect on the Earth's atmosphere, known as thunder.
/m/0jb2l.name: Thunderstorm

/m/0284vy3.description: The sound of an air horn which serves as an audible warning device on diesel and electric locomotives.
/m/0284vy3.name: Train horn

/m/07n_g.description: The sound of an acoustic resonator in the form of a two-pronged fork with the prongs formed from a U-shaped bar of elastic metal. It emits a pure musical tone and is frequently used as a standard of pitch to tune musical instruments.
/m/07n_g.name: Tuning fork

/m/025_jnm.description: A snapping or clicking sound usually caused by building tension between the thumb and another finger and then moving the other finger forcefully downward to hits the palm at high speed.
/m/025_jnm.name: Finger snapping

/m/05szwhw.description: The sound of a simple linear resonator in free oscillation in response to an impulse of excitation, usually ending in an exponentially decaying sine tone.
/m/05szwhw.name: Ringing (of resonator)

/m/0ytgt.description: Speech uttered by a human child, i.e. a human whose voice does not yet resemble that of an adult.
/m/0ytgt.name: Child speech, kid speaking

/m/05r5c.description: Sounds of a musical instrument played via a row of keys that the performer presses down or strikes with the fingers and thumbs of both hands, to trigger a decaying note whose loudness reflects the vigor of the press.
/m/05r5c.name: Piano

/m/083vt.description: Sounds associated with the porous and fibrous structural tissue found in the stems and roots of trees, and other woody plants.
comments_EF: difficult to narrow down. will probably be noisy
/m/083vt.name: Wood

/m/07ryjzk.description: The sharp sound of a flat object striking another (e.g., an open hand hitting a face).
/m/07ryjzk.name: Slap, smack

/m/053hz1.description: Encouraging, stimulating, or exciting vocalizations indicating approval or welcoming persons, announcements, etc.
/m/053hz1.name: Cheering

/m/0jtg0.description: Sounds of a plucked stringed instrument used mainly in Hindustani and Indian classical music, which derives its distinctive timbre and resonance from sympathetic strings, bridge design, a long hollow neck, and a gourd-shaped resonance chamber.
/m/0jtg0.name: Sitar

/m/02rr_.description: Sounds associated with an electronic device that alters how a musical instrument or other audio source sounds. Some effects subtly "color" a sound while others transform it dramatically.
/m/02rr_.name: Effects unit

/m/07s02z0.description: A short, high-pitched tone without a sharp attack and with a perceptible variation in pitch.
/m/07s02z0.name: Squeal

/m/0239kh.description: A simple metal bell historically tied around the necks of cattle to keep track of their whereabouts.
/m/0239kh.name: Cowbell

/m/04fq5q.description: A signaling sound used primarily in foggy conditions to warn watercraft of the presence of nearby vessels or other navigational hazards.
/m/04fq5q.name: Foghorn

/m/07c6l.description: The sound of a brass instrument that includes a telescoping slide mechanism that varies the length of the instrument to change the pitch.
/m/07c6l.name: Trombone

/m/03q5_w.description: The release of gas from the digestive tract through the mouth.
/m/03q5_w.name: Burping, eructation

/m/0mkg.description: The sound of a family of box-shaped bellows-driven musical instruments played by pressing buttons or keys which allow air to flow across strips of brass or steel, called reeds, that vibrate to produce sound inside the body.
/m/0mkg.name: Accordion

/t/dd00099.description: Sounds of impacts or collisions preferentially described by their acoustic properties, rather than by immediately referring to their assumed source object(s).
/t/dd00099.name: Generic impact sounds

/t/dd00130.description: The sound of an engine starting from rest, which may involve a specific starter mechanism (as in a standard car).
/t/dd00130.name: Engine starting

/m/06w87.description: Sounds of a guitar whose string length is controlled by a hard object placed on the string (the "slide" or "steel") instead of by pressing against the frets with the fingers.
/m/06w87.name: Steel guitar, slide guitar

/m/06hck5.description: The sound of a device used to produce sound with the aid of live steam, which acts as a vibrating system.
/m/06hck5.name: Steam whistle

/m/06bz3.description: A sound that appears to have been produced by a radio receiver.
/m/06bz3.name: Radio

/t/dd00033.description: Music that evokes or conveys feelings of sadness.
/t/dd00033.name: Sad music

/t/dd00013.description: The sound of children at play, including any of vocalization or the sounds of their activities.
/t/dd00013.name: Children playing

/m/0k65p.description: Sounds originating primarily from the hands and fingers of humans.
/m/0k65p.name: Hands

/m/0319l.description: The sound of a brass instrument made of tubing wrapped into a coil with a flared bell. A modern French horn includes valves to control pitch by routing air into extra sections of tubing.
/m/0319l.name: French horn

/m/07qcx4z.description: The sound of a flat or smooth surface separating abruptly.
/m/07qcx4z.name: Tearing

/m/02fxyj.description: A wordless tone produced by forcing the sound to emerge from the nose, often with a melody.
/m/02fxyj.comments_XF: Precision problem here.... 'hum' used in different context
/m/02fxyj.name: Humming

/m/07rbp7_.description: The sound of whipping, i.e., the greatly accelerated motion of the tip of a flexible structure, as the result of concentrated angular momentum.
/m/07rbp7_.name: Whip

/m/0gy1t2s.description: The sound of a percussive signaling instrument mounted on a bicycle for warning pedestrians and other cyclists.
/m/0gy1t2s.name: Bicycle bell

/m/07bgp.description: Sounds associated with the familiar quadrupedal, ruminant mammal typically kept as livestock.
/m/07bgp.name: Sheep

/m/03q5t.description: Sounds of a keyboard-controlled instrument in which each key plucks a particular string.
/m/03q5t.name: Harpsichord

/m/07sr1lc.description: Utter or declare in a very loud voice that seems excessive or involuntary, or that is deliberately startling in order to command attention, as distinct from the pragmatically raised voice of Shout.
/m/07sr1lc.name: Yell

/m/0bm0k.description: The sound of a cymbal that produces a loud, sharp "crash" used for occasional accents.
/m/0bm0k.name: Crash cymbal

/m/07qb_dv.description: The sound of a hard, sharp point of contact leaving a permanent groove in a hard surface.
/m/07qb_dv.name: Scratch

/m/020bb7.description: Bird communication calls, often considered melodious to the human ear.
/m/020bb7.name: Bird vocalization, bird call, bird song

/m/0193bn.description: The sound associated with the shock waves created by an object traveling through the air faster than the speed of sound.
/m/0193bn.name: Sonic boom

/m/032s66.description: The sound of the discharge of a firearm, or multiple such discharges.
/m/032s66.comments_XF: where are the sounds of reloading guns??
/m/032s66.name: Gunshot, gunfire

/m/0ln16.description: A genre of music that is based largely on Cuban, Puerto Rican, and Dominican popular dance music, occasionally incorporating elements of rock, R&B, and funk.
/m/0ln16.name: Salsa music

/m/07pjwq1.description: The sound of rapid vibration, commonly the wings of a flying insect.
/m/07pjwq1.name: Buzz

/m/07cx4.description: The sound of a telecommunications device that permits two or more users to conduct a conversation when they are too far apart to be heard directly.  This class covers sounds associated with the device itself, not voice that has been carried via the telephone network.
/m/07cx4.name: Telephone

/m/06q74.description: The sound of a large buoyant watercraft, distinguished from boats based on size, shape, and cargo or passenger capacity.
/m/06q74.name: Ship

/m/07p78v5.description: A brief high-pitched buzzing or humming sound.
/m/07p78v5.name: Zing

/m/07qc9xj.description: A short, pitchless, transient sound, as of a gentle impact between small hard objects.
/m/07qc9xj.name: Clicking

/m/07pczhz.description: The sound of cutting a solid material such as wood into smaller pieces by using an ax or other hacking tool.
/m/07pczhz.name: Chop

/m/03cczk.description: Food being crushed and ground by teeth.
/m/03cczk.name: Chewing, mastication
